0),(75,8,'2014-06-05 18:29:08','2014-06-05 12:59:08','<strong>Who are we?</strong>\n\nWe are a group of IIT Delhi students, who believe that there\'s an urgent need for something to be done with regards to Safety of The Indian Roads.\n\n<strong>What are we trying to Do?</strong>\n\nThrough a petition signed by about 1,00,000 people, we aim to put pressure on the Indian National Government to put in policies, rules and regulations that would control the scourge of death, disabilities and injuries resulting from road traffic crashes in India. Please sign the petition and support us.\n\n<a title=\"File petition now\" href=\"http://chn.ge/1otxm8n\">http://chn.ge/1otxm8n</a>\n\n<strong>Why did we start?</strong>\n\nThe death of 4 our colleagues in a car accident was a brutal eye opener for us. After the tragic incident we were figuring out ideas as to what can be done so that these accidents can be avoided. We were sitting in our class of BML330, the traffic safety course, Professor Dinesh Mohan gave us an idea for a petition to put pressure on the government, the idea felt like a way through which we could make a real difference. A few of us met up with few other professors and brainstormed a letter which we will be sending to the Prime minister of the country as well as the chief Minister of all the states. The letter would contain our sentiments, demanding safer roads and safety policies that are needed to be implemented on an urgent basis.\n\nLink To the Petition\n<a title=\"File petition now\" href=\"http://chn.ge/1otxm8n\">http://chn.ge/1otxm8n</a>\n\nLike us on <a title=\"Facebook\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/RoadSafetyIITD\"> Facebook</a>\nOR\nFollow us on <a title=\"Twitter\" href=\" https://twitter.com/RoadSafetyIITD\"> Twitter</a>\n\n[su_youtube url=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oDetNxaotOY\"]\n\nIf you would like to help Contact us at roadsafetycampaigniitd@gmail.com','Indian road safety campaign by IITD students','','publish','open','open','','indian-road-safety-campaign-iitd','','','2014-06-05 18:29:08','2014-06-05 12:59:08','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=75',0,'post','',4),(219,2,'2014-06-10 23:53:39','2014-06-10 18:23:39','[vc_accordion width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"] [vc_accordion_tab title=\"What does Helpiez do?\"] [vc_column_text width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\n\nHelpiez in a nut shell is a web portal, a interactive website through which the users , especially the youth with their extensive social circles and network can connect to welfare organisations and the society. The web portal will feature customizable search options for all the projects, programs, volunteering events, internships or jobs related to NGOs etc. It will also have a separate profile for each organisation which they get to manage according to their needs.\n\n[/vc_column_text] [/vc_accordion_tab] [vc_accordion_tab title=\"What does Helpiez want to gain from its venture?\"] [vc_column_text width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\n\nThis portal will directly help welfare organisations in increasing their online presence which will enable people to look through their agenda and contribute correspondingly. Hence, it will increase awareness in the society for both the Cause and about the NGO which works for the Cause. It will also motivate the masses to do community service and volunteer with the organisation of their choice. Also, the process of volunteering for social cause will become easy and efficient.\n\n[/vc_column_text] [/vc_accordion_tab] [vc_accordion_tab title=\"What are the other issues that Helpiez cater to?\"] [vc_column_text width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\n\nApart from the bigger picture of bridging the distance between NGO\'s and the people, Helpiez also actively works for those issues that plagues are society and threatens the very existence of it. The list includes:\n\n<a href=\"art-culture\">Art and Culture </a>|<a href=\"Civil-Rights\"> Civil rights and Transparency </a>|<a href=\"#\"> Community Development </a>|<a href=\"#\"> Disaster Management</a>|<a href=\"#\"> Education and employment</a>|<a href=\"#\"> Empowering Disabled</a>|<a href=\"#\"> Environment </a>|<a href=\"#\"> Health Issues </a>|<a href=\"#\"> Human Development </a>|<a href=\"#\"> Politics </a>|<a href=\"#\"> Religion </a>|<a href=\"#\"> Save the Animals </a>|<a href=\"#\"> Safety </a>|<a href=\"#\"> Violence and Discrimination </a>|<a href=\"#\"> Women\'s Issues</a>\n\n[/vc_column_text] [/vc_accordion_tab] [vc_accordion_tab title=\"Whom Do we work with?\"] [vc_column_text width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\n\nOur organization teams up with various NGO\'s that are located in Delhi and NCR region of the country and extend their services to them. Apart from that we also collaborate the NSS Societies from various colleges in Delhi.\n\n[/vc_column_text] [/vc_accordion_tab] [vc_accordion_tab title=\"Who supports the organization?\"] [vc_column_text width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\n\nSince Helpiez is right now in its earliest stages, no corporate company supports our cause but being the brain child of IIT Delhi, Helpiez is supported by various NSS programs from IIT Delhi.\n\n[/vc_column_text] [/vc_accordion_tab] [/vc_accordion]','Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)','','publish','open','open','','faq','','','2014-06-10 23:53:39','2014-06-10 18:23:39','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?page_id=219',0,'page','',0),(238,5,'2014-06-11 10:48:06','2014-06-11 05:18:06','','Notorious Elephant Abuser Tim Frisco Makes Baby Elephant, Val, Stand on Her Head-She Screams.','','inherit','open','open','','notorious-elephant-abuser-tim-frisco-makes-baby-elephant-val-stand-on-her-head-she-screams','','','2014-06-11 10:48:06','2014-06-11 05:18:06','',0,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/notorious-elephant-abuser-tim-frisco-makes-baby-elephant-val-stand-on-her-head-she-screams.mp4',0,'attachment','video/mp4',0),(286,5,'2014-06-11 18:04:16','2014-06-11 12:34:16','[video width=\"480\" height=\"360\" mp4=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/notorious-elephant-abuser-tim-frisco-makes-baby-elephant-val-stand-on-her-head-she-screams.mp4\"][/video]\n\n<br></br> \nHelp protect animals from horrendous abuse! Please sign this important petition (<a href=\"https://www.change.org/petitions/house-committee-on-agriculture-livestock-rural-development-and-credit-support-h-r-4525-traveling-exotic-animal-protection-act\">Sign here</a>) to help protect animals such as elephants, lions and other \"exotic\" animals from a lifetime of cruelty\nIn order to \"train\" wild animals to perform, they\'re abused, and reactions are attained using negative reinforcement from humans physically striking them using their hands, whips, and bullhooks; often electric shock prods are also used. Animals that are forced to perform during entertainment shows are housed in small, temporary facilities and/or also restricted via chains to minimize mobility. Also, during arduous journeys between performance locations, they\'re again housed in cramped areas and elephants are also chained. During travel, the creatures are forced to live in their feces and urine.\n\nAll of this abuse, living conditions, and overall inhumane treatment of wild animals leads to physical ailments, stress, trauma and often leads to death. There have been several documented cases of circus animals having physical injuries from bullhooks, diseases, lack of veterinary care, and mental stress that is portrayed by the body pacing, rocking, swaying heads; all of this leads to animals \"snapping\" and posing threat to the public, which leads to animals being gunned down in cities.\n\nAlmost 30 countries have taken action to end animal cruelty that stems from traveling circuses and it\'s time for the U.S. to do so as well. I understand circuses have been a part of our culture, but we shouldn\'t subject animals to a lifetime of trauma and a grueling death for the sake of entertainment.\n<a href=\"https://www.change.org/petitions/house-committee-on-agriculture-livestock-rural-development-and-credit-support-h-r-4525-traveling-exotic-animal-protection-act\">Sign here</a>','Animal cruelty','','publish','open','open','','animal-cruelty','','','2014-06-11 18:04:16','2014-06-11 12:34:16','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=286',0,'post','',0),(310,2,'2014-06-12 00:55:26','2014-06-11 19:25:26','Helpiez database comes under creative commons license   ','Creative Commons','Helpiez database comes under creative commons license   ','inherit','open','open','','download-4','','','2014-06-12 00:55:26','2014-06-11 19:25:26','',0,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/download-4.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(317,2,'2014-06-12 12:09:56','2014-06-12 06:39:56','Thanks for visiting us. We’d like to make sure that you reach out to us in the best way possible, like we reach out to you everyday. Thus, we try to make it as easy as possible for you to connect with us. You can either connect with us via various social networking options, send an email to support@helpiez.org or leave us a message below.\n\n[contact-form-7 id=\"2184\" title=\"contactus\"]','Contact us','We like to meet new people working for social cause . Feel free to contact us whenever you like .','publish','closed','open','','contact','','','2014-06-12 12:09:56','2014-06-12 06:39:56','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?page_id=317',0,'page','',0),(362,2,'2014-06-12 21:48:53','2014-06-12 16:18:53','If you have any suggestion please feel free to write to us.\n[contact-form-7 id=\"1440\" title=\"email\"]\n','Feedback and Suggestions','','publish','closed','closed','','feedback','','','2014-06-12 21:48:53','2014-06-12 16:18:53','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?page_id=362',0,'page','',0),(467,2,'2014-06-19 17:44:19','2014-06-19 12:14:19','','favicon','','inherit','open','open','','favicon-2','','','2014-06-19 17:44:19','2014-06-19 12:14:19','',0,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/favicon1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(470,2,'2014-06-20 00:15:37','2014-06-19 18:45:37','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We are glad that you are here. Currently we are making database of Delhi NCR region NGOs only. If you want to add NGO which is not in Delhi mail us on support@helpiez.org.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Before adding any NGO check whether it is present in database or not  by searching its name <a title=\"here\" href=\"/search\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> . If  it is already there you can edit/add info there only by pressing green button present on NGO page. The instructions for each field to be filled are as follows :-</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Name - </strong>Write Name with proper spacing. If name is an acronym write full form in brackets.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Address - </strong>Give the Address of regional head office .</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Region </strong>Select appropriate Region where NGO works.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Contact Number - </strong>Put \'011\'  before landline and ‘+91-‘ before mobile phone. If there are more than one please write all important contact number.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Weblink - </strong>Write full website link like https://www.helpiez.com don\'t forget http://</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong> Youtube - </strong>Find a video on youtube that best describe that NGO and its work. And then give only the ID of video from its URL.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">  For ex – From URL  <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DQMvT8XwdR8\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DQMvT8XwdR8</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">                We want only ‘DQMvT8XwdR8’ in column</p>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Description - </strong>Write description of the NGO work. Try to write at least 5-6 lines.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Facebook -</strong> Give only page name from URLFor ex- <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pravahdelhi\">https://www.facebook.com/pravahdelhi</a> give only ‘pravahdelhi’</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Blog url – </strong>Give complete url don\'t forget http://</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Twitter_Handle –</strong>Give twitter handle (don’t put @ in beginning ) For ex @pravahdelhi is twitter handle of pravah give only \'pravahdelhi\' in text field.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Beneficiary - </strong>Check all the beneficiary whom the NGO is Helping.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Causes</strong> - Check all the cause for which NGO is working</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Skills</strong> - Write the key skills which NGO is using while working towards the cause.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Key - </strong>Your name is the key. Write your name and theNGO will be added in our database . We are taking names just for rewarding your contribution.</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Contact Number or Email - </strong>Don\'t worry your Email and phone number will not be published and it is safe with us . It is just for identifying the contributor for acknowledgement purpose.</li>\n</ol>\nThank you. Hope your contribution will help many people. ;)\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_310\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"205\"]<a href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/\"><img class=\"wp-image-310\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/download-4-300x113.jpg\" alt=\"Helpiez Creative common adding\" width=\"205\" height=\"74\" /></a> Helpiez database license[/caption]\n\n&nbsp;\n\nIf you have any thoughts please be frank to comment below','Instruction for adding new NGO','','publish','open','open','','add-instruct','','','2014-06-20 00:15:37','2014-06-19 18:45:37','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?page_id=470',0,'page','',0),(502,2,'2014-06-20 00:42:25','2014-06-19 19:12:25','','earth_is_life','Earth and its creatures','inherit','open','open','','earth_is_life','','','2014-06-20 00:42:25','2014-06-19 19:12:25','',470,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/earth_is_life.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(577,2,'2014-06-22 22:24:02','2014-06-22 16:54:02','','World_Map_Index_of_perception_of_corruption.svg','Corruption perception country wise','inherit','open','open','','world_map_index_of_perception_of_corruption-svg','','','2014-06-22 22:24:02','2014-06-22 16:54:02','',0,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/world_map_index_of_perception_of_corruption.svg_.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(590,2,'2014-06-22 23:01:18','2014-06-22 17:31:18','','STOP_GLOBAL_WARMING_AND_SAVE_THE_TREES','Save Environment ','inherit','open','open','','stop_global_warming_and_save_the_trees','','','2014-06-22 23:01:18','2014-06-22 17:31:18','',0,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/stop_global_warming_and_save_the_trees.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(593,2,'2014-06-22 23:09:30','2014-06-22 17:39:30','','Mother earth','Save the environment','inherit','open','open','','5767445628_2bb87e734d_z','','','2014-06-22 23:09:30','2014-06-22 17:39:30','',0,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/5767445628_2bb87e734d_z-e1403458998551.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(594,2,'2014-06-22 23:11:09','2014-06-22 17:41:09','','earth','Save environment','inherit','open','open','','5767445628_2bb87e734d_z-2','','','2014-06-22 23:11:09','2014-06-22 17:41:09','',0,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/5767445628_2bb87e734d_z1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jp