8:51:35','',0,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/dazi-e1420968467113.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1358,3,'2014-07-24 00:23:47','2014-07-23 18:53:47','','Mohit','','inherit','open','open','','mohit','','','2014-07-24 00:23:47','2014-07-23 18:53:47','',0,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/mohit.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1359,3,'2014-07-24 00:23:53','2014-07-23 18:53:53','','Pooja','','inherit','open','open','','pooja','','','2014-07-24 00:23:53','2014-07-23 18:53:53','',0,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/pooja.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1360,3,'2014-07-24 00:23:59','2014-07-23 18:53:59','','Rahul','','inherit','open','open','','rahul','','','2014-07-24 00:23:59','2014-07-23 18:53:59','',0,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/rahul.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1392,5,'2014-08-01 23:31:03','2014-08-01 18:01:03','&nbsp;\n\nSocial work is many things, like helping individuals improve their lives, assisting groups in accessing needed services and guiding communities to effect change. Professionals in the field of social work have a tremendous responsibility in their involvement with people.\n\n<strong>Definition</strong>\n\nSocial workers help individuals, communities and groups to either enhance or restore their ability for social functioning.\n\n<strong>Helping</strong>\nSocial work is a \"helping\" profession; the professionals in this field assess their clients and determine their strengths and needs, soliciting their ideas about what they want to accomplish.\n\n<strong>Community</strong>\nThe social worker\'s \"client\" can also be a community, such as several at-risk youth needing an outlet for their energy and creativity. Here, the social worker assists them as they decide how to help themselves.\n\n<strong>Services</strong>\nSocial workers help their clients access needed services; they can also help access \"hard\" services such as a food bank.\n\n<strong>Human Development</strong>\nSocial workers have to understand human development from birth to death in order to better help his clients.\n\n<strong>Societal Systems</strong>\nThe social worker should also understand the systems in our society; he will be better able to facilitate his clients as they establish their niche in these systems.','Definition of social work','','publish','open','open','','definition-social-work','','','2014-08-01 23:31:03','2014-08-01 18:01:03','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1392',0,'post','',0),(1394,5,'2014-08-01 23:30:30','2014-08-01 18:00:30','','images (1)','','inherit','open','open','','images-1','','','2014-08-01 23:30:30','2014-08-01 18:00:30','',1392,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1413,6,'2014-08-03 21:39:44','2014-08-03 16:09:44','','proof','','inherit','open','open','','proof','','','2014-08-03 21:39:44','2014-08-03 16:09:44','',0,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/proof.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1428,2,'2014-08-18 19:54:39','2014-08-18 14:24:39','','Anser_indicus_Dadri_wetlands','','inherit','open','open','','anser_indicus_dadri_wetlands','','','2014-08-18 19:54:39','2014-08-18 14:24:39','',850,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/anser_indicus_dadri_wetlands.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1435,2,'2014-08-22 16:05:11','2014-08-22 10:35:11','','10371985_652061188206352_6733853034672175316_n','','inherit','open','open','','10371985_652061188206352_6733853034672175316_n','','','2014-08-22 16:05:11','2014-08-22 10:35:11','',75,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/10371985_652061188206352_6733853034672175316_n.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1456,5,'2014-09-17 21:51:35','2014-09-17 16:21:35','Just go right through the bullshit, talking about samotypes. There are three types of body types : Ectomorph Mesomorph Endomorph\n\n&nbsp;\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You probably have heard about this term before. Ectomorph is classified as who is skinny ,small bone structure, fast metabolism typically known as a horrid gainer , they find it difficult to gain mass muscle. Then we have mesomorph someone who is naturally a bigger, thicker bone structure, metabolism right in the middle somewhere, easily put on muscle and doesn’t find it difficult to put on mass muscle and lastly we have endomorph typically refer to may be as fat, slow metabolism , lazy , more round shape, find hard to put on muscles and find hard to burn off fat .</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><em>So what’s the problem?</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The problem we have with body type and classifying yourself under one of these body types is bone structure does not determine your metabolism. So when you place yourself under one of these categories , you have already taken away your own ability mentally to get pass that characteristic. So you stop thinking that you are an ectomorph and you never gone a build muscles. You can actually take that ectomorph part out by taking nutrition ,training down , progressively overload eat in surplus you have to take rest ,show dedication, consistency , patience all will help you to gain muscles.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you really want something better than you have to work for it , if you think you are ectomorph take that label off of yourself and become a mesomorph, get ready for action in gym and work hard for it , so somatotype is a bullshit as for as your physique goes and body composition I certainly believe it is . So it ok if you classify under certain bone structure, some people do have thicker ankle, thicker wrist, more stocky structure but by no mean should body type takeover your ability to control your physique that’s my personal opinion. Some people truly believe in somatotype and think that there are special diet and training routine for each category which is not true.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You can see product marketed exclusively for each body type, which seems to be pathetic .People are spending money on something that gives them false hope because they were told that they are ectomorph and they have to follow this particular diet and training procedure in order to put on muscles but it doesn’t work like that, if someone is classifying you under one of the body types then don’t get depressed keep basic funda of working hard, try to focus on your basic training principles put your 3D that is dedication ,devotion and determination and you will achieve what you aspire for ,that’s my opinion on this whole topic</p>','The Somatype Myth : Understanding your body types','','publish','open','open','','somatype-myth-understanding-body-types','','','2014-09-17 21:51:35','2014-09-17 16:21:35','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1456',0,'post','',0),(1457,2,'2014-09-17 21:40:31','2014-09-17 16:10:31','','body-type-chart-ectomorph','','inherit','open','open','','body-type-chart-ectomorph','','','2014-09-17 21:40:31','2014-09-17 16:10:31','',1456,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/body-type-chart-ectomorph.gif',0,'attachment','image/gif',0),(1475,5,'2014-09-22 22:44:04','2014-09-22 17:14:04','&nbsp;\n\nGetting six-pack abs is not a difficult task when you do it the right way. Recent researches show that diet plan controls about 70 per cent of your weight loss but that does not mean that exercise isn\'t important.We all have abs but they are hidden due to the coverage of fat. In order to define and flaunt them, one must eat right and exercise.It is rightly said that abs are made in the kitchen. This is because, you need to follow a strict diet in order to get them and also maintain them.\n\n&nbsp;\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The rule is to Start eating 5-6 meals per day (space them out to about one every 3 hours). You are eating more often, but not necessarily more.So if you are eating often and eating good food, you would not have cravings for any kind of junk food. It will also help regulate your body’s blood sugar, which stabilizes the release of insulin. This helps promote the use of fat as fuel and helps prevent it from being stored in the body. When excess fat isn’t stored, the abs are more prominent.</p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Training Day Meal</strong>\n\n• Early morning: 1-2 glass water\n• 8-9 am: Breakfast\n• 11-12 pm: Snack\n• 1-2 pm: Lunch\n• 4-5pm: Snack\n• 7-8 pm: Dinner\n• 9-10 pm (if hungry): Milk\n\n<a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/download.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1477 size-full\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/download.jpg\" alt=\"diet plan\" width=\"278\" height=\"181\" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n•<strong> Meal 1:</strong>\n\n10 egg whites+1 cups oatmeal (dry measure) +1 apple +1banana +1 protein shake+1 glass skimmed milk\n• <strong>Meal 2:</strong>\n200 gm paneer+2 gauva + ½ papaya + 1 cup green tea\n\n• <strong>Meal 3:</strong> (lunch)\n3 roti +vegetable+ pulse + salad\n\n•<strong> Meal 4</strong> : (pre work out )\n2 banana +1 black coffee +1 protein shake\n• <strong>Meal 5</strong> :(post workout)\n\n5 egg white+ 1 banana+ 1 protein shake\n• <strong>Meal 6</strong> :(Dinner)\n2 roti + pulse + vegetable\n\nBefore going to bed 1 glass skimmed milk\n\nIncrease your protein intake. Without protein your body cannot build new muscle. Protein also helps to increase your metabolism -- which burns calories.\n\n<strong>Proteins:</strong>\nProtein acts as the building block for muscles but doesn\'t bulk up the muscles, a myth that many people carry. The only way to bulk up muscles is to hit the gym and perform progressive resistance exercises. Protein helps provide the raw material to build muscle, but the protein has to be pulled into muscles through exercise.\n\n<strong>Hydration:</strong>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is very important to keep yourself hydrated. Water is an essential nutrient that is involved in every function of the body. Except for oxygen, there’s nothing your body needs more than an adequate supply of water. And the more you exercise, the more important it is to drink the right amount of water before, during, and after your workouts. Dehydration can make it hard to get the most out of your workout and in extreme situations, can even be dangerous to your health.</p>\n<strong> Good carbohydrates:</strong>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Carbohydrate is undoubtedly the most important source of energy for workout. No matter what exercise you do, carbs provide the energy that fuels muscle contractions. Once eaten, carbohydrates breakdown into smaller sugars (glucose, fructose and galactose) that get absorbed and used as energy.\nAny glucose not needed right away gets stored in the muscles and the liver in the form of glycogen. Once these glycogen stores are filled up, any extra gets stored as fat. Adequate carbohydrate intake also helps prevent protein from being used as energy. If the body doesn\'t have enough carbohydrate, protein is broken down to make glucose for energy.\nFruits and veggies: Fruits and veggies provide you with all the nutrients and fiber which is required by our body. They are a storehouse of various nutrients and are a must-have if you want a fit body with six-pack abs.\nAll of us have 6-packs abs in our bodies but they are usually hidden under a layer of fat. When we work out, they become prominent as the fat decreases from that area and the muscles become visible.</p>\n<a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/download-12.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1481 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/download-12.jpg\" alt=\"download (1)\" width=\"264\" height=\"191\" /></a>\nYes, they are largely a result of what you eat and not just what you do in the gym. In order to eat right, one should:\n\n• Eat frequent, small meals.\n• Have protein in every meal\n• Avoid foods with trans-fats, too much sugar, fattening junk food, add more fiber, good carbs in the form of whole wheat pasta, soy, greens, white meat, etc.\n\n<strong>Timing is Key</strong>\nMeal timing is the other key to staying lean while bulking up. When you eat not only supports mass gains but also plays a pivotal role in controlling body fat levels. If you’re trying to gain only quality mass, increase the size of your meals at breakfast and after training. These are the two times of day when muscles crave more calories and nutrients—at breakfast because you’re nutritionally depleted after a night’s sleep, and post-workout because the stressed muscles are in dire need of replenishment to jump-start the recovery process. Providing the body with what it can put to use during these windows facilitates optimum growth and keeps body fat levels down.','Diet plan and some facts about gaining mass muscles','','publish','open','open','','whole-diet-plan','','','2014-09-22 22:44:04','2014-09-22 17:14:04','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1475',0,'post','',1),(1477,2,'2014-09-22 22:05:41','2014-09-22 16:35:41','','download','','inherit','open','open','','download','','','2014-09-22 22:05:41','2014-09-22 16:35:41','',1475,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/download.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1478,2,'2014-09-22 22:07:16','2014-09-22 16:37:16','','images (3)','','inherit','open','open','','images-3','','','2014-09-22 22:07:16','2014-09-22 16:37:16','',1475,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1480,2,'2014-09-22 22:20:06','2014-09-22 16:50:06','','images (4)','','inherit','open','open','','images-4','','','2014-09-22 22:20:06','2014-09-22 16:50:06','',1475,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-4.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1481,2,'2014-09-22 22:22:44','2014-09-22 16:52:44','','download (1)','','inherit','open','open','','download-1-2','','','2014-09-22 22:22:44','2014-09-22 16:52:44','',1475,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/download-12.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1496,9,'2014-10-14 15:53:55','2014-10-14 10:23:55','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\nThe other day while going through Posts on my Facebook account, one pic caught my eye. It Read..\n\n<strong><em>\' India is 1.3 Billion Strong....Still it lacks a world class football team.! \' </em></strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nNow that made ..rather FORCED me to think about the reason....\'<strong>CAUSE</strong>\' for this <strong>Pathetic</strong> condition of Indian Sports.\n\nExcept Cricket..can you think of any other sports where <strong>WE INDIANS</strong> are in the  <strong>APEX</strong> position ?\n\nForget being First....Top 3..or Top 5 ??\n\nNah..!\n\nI don\'t know what the Readers\' answer will be but what I feel is ...\n\nWe could have had great Football..Basketball...Handball Players but probably they are Engineers or Doctors right now.\n\nIt was reported in some informative site that as soon as a Chinese Baby turns 2, Parents drop that baby in the swimming pool or send it to a local athletic club.\n\nIntially I doubted this report ...\n\nBut after looking at the Medal Tally of  Asian Games, I had no option but to believe.\n\nThe Honourable Prime Minister of <strong>HINDUSTAN, </strong>during his recent visit to STATES said -\n\n\" India is the world\'s Largest Democracy...\n\nIndia is one of the best and beloved Tourist Spot in the World..\n\nIndia is this ..India is That.....\"\n\nAnd the Galaxy of Intellectuals witnessing  the speech were all listening to NaMo with rapt attention and nodding in affirmative.\n\nIndia is one of the world\'s fastest growing economy...Military Power.. Motherland for Computer Language.\n\nEven the World Famous author like Mark Twain coudn\'t help but  appreciate India\'s beauty and culture.\n\nSuch A Great Nation is India...\n\nBut isnt it depressing that even after achieving such greatness,  Sports Persons in India are given no importance ?\n\nBefore, Olympic Medal Winner KD Jadhav had to sell his medal in order to fund his Medical Expenses and Now a Mountaineer...A person who scaled Mt Everest has to sell Vegetables in order to feed his stomach.\n\nThere are people who, after doing <strong>ABSOLUTELY NOTHING </strong> own thousands of Acres...Hundreds of Crores of Money..Thousands of Silk Sarees..Tonnes of Gold and Silver and on the other side there are people who after winning Medals..bringing Laurels to the Country get a Rs. 10000/- PM job by Government and spend thier lives.\n\nIf a Celebrity is getting Married, our Media provides us with 24 hrs of LIVE coverage and If one of our players become victim of biasses,  Media shrugs off from their responsibilities.\n\nSupporting and Encouraging budding Sports Enthusiasts is the need of the hour or the day will come when India will be completely vanished from the Medal Tally..be it be Olympics, CWG or ASIAN Games.\n\nThose who think that this cannot be changed or repaired, remember -\n\n<strong>\' PEOPLE WHO ARE CRAZY ENOUGH TO THINK THEY CAN CHANGE THE WORLD....</strong>\n\n<strong>ARE THE ONES WHO ACTUALLY DO IT..!!\' </strong>\n\n<strong>JAI HIND !!</strong>\n\n&nbsp;','Pathetic condition of Sports in India.','Pathetic condition of sports in India','publish','open','open','','pathetic-condition-of-sports-in-india','','','2014-10-14 15:53:55','2014-10-14 10:23:55','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1496',0,'post','',0),(1497,2,'2014-10-14 15:44:51','2014-10-14 10:14:51','','frg','','inherit','open','open','','frg','','','2014-10-14 15:44:51','2014-10-14 10:14:51','',1496,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/frg.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1501,9,'2014-10-15 14:14:10','2014-10-15 08:44:10','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/download-21.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1502\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/download-21.jpg\" alt=\"download (2)\" width=\"259\" height=\"194\" /></a></p>\n&nbsp;\n\nYesterday, Rakesh Bhandari , an IT employee succumbed to Ebola virus disease in Pune. India, is getting infected with Ebola at an alrming rate lately.\n\nEbola toll has crossed 4000 worldwide, which is a big concern.\n\nEbola virus disease is caused by four or five viruses classified in the genus <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ebolavirus\"><em>Ebolavirus</em></a>, family <em><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Filoviridae\">Filoviridae</a></em> and order <em><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mononegavirales\">Mononegavirales</a></em>.  It is also transmitted from Human to Human and Animal to Human.\n\nAs it is a Viral Disease, Finding a cure is not an easy task.\n\nSymptoms include – Viral Fever, Severe Weight loss, Chest pain, Red Eyes and Diarrhea.\n\nBut as we all know <strong>Precaution is always better than cure..!</strong>\n\nThere are some precautions which we are supposed to take in order to safeguard our-self and our family from this dreaded disease.\n<ul>\n	<li>If possible, Honey should be consumed as much as possible.</li>\n	<li>Traditional Vaccine includes taking bath in cold water and drinking hot water. Water plays an important role in controlling virsues.</li>\n	<li>Just like in the case of Swine Flue, hands should be washed frequently .</li>\n	<li>Places of outbreaks should be avoided and remains of Ebola Victims should not be manhandled, as even their remains are contagious.</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\nI am sure if these precautions are followed strictly, we can keep Ebola virus at bay.\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/ebola-virus.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1503\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/ebola-virus.png\" alt=\"ebola-virus\" width=\"628\" height=\"350\" /></a></p>\n&nbsp;\n\nIf any Ebola Victim is in your vicinity please contact :-\n\n<strong>Emergency Operation Centre </strong><strong>011- 23061469 , 3205 and 1302</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>KEEP CALM AND STAY SAFE</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>JAI HIND !</strong>','The plague of Ebola Virus Disease','Ebola toll has crossed 4000 worldwide. some precautions which we are supposed to take in order to safeguard our-self and our family from this dreaded disease.','publish','open','open','','ebola-virus-disease','','','2014-10-15 14:14:10','2014-10-15 08:44:10','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1501',0,'post','',0),(1502,2,'2014-10-15 14:02:06','2014-10-15 08:32:06','','download (2)','','inherit','open','open','','download-2-2','','','2014-10-15 14:02:06','2014-10-15 08:32:06','',1501,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/download-21.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1503,2,'2014-10-15 14:03:04','2014-10-15 08:33:04','','ebola-virus','','inherit','open','open','','ebola-virus','','','2014-10-15 14:03:04','2014-10-15 08:33:04','',1501,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/ebola-virus.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1514,9,'2014-10-23 16:41:11','2014-10-23 11:11:11','Diwali is being celebrated in India for thousands of years . \nWhen Lord Ram came back to Ayodhya after defeating King Ravana in Sri Lanka, The Ayodhdians were so happy and excited that they lit up the entire city with lights and crackers around. \n\nDiwali, although a festival of 3-4 days holds lots of significance. Lights , Crackers and delicacies are the main factors associated with the Festival. \nIts during this time when Neighbours, Friends and Relatives come together for the celebration exchanging Sweets and new dresses. \nBut this generation has a wrong perception about the festival. They relate Diwali as a festival where crackers are burst, nothing else which is totally wrong. \nMumbai alone spends around 600 crs. of money on Crackers. So just imagine how much money our nation must be  spending oncrackers annually. \nThis money if used for some other noble cause can result in a huge, massive wave of change-improvement in India. \nInstead of wasting money, people collectively should donate the money to some needy or an organization forking for social good.\nSpend the money by organizing some kind of programs so that quality time with Well wishers can be spent. \n\nIf we all rack our brains we can find numerous ways to spend our ‘CRACKERS’ money on some good stuffs. \n\nThis Diwali, lets PROMISE ourselves that instead of lighting up the sky and polluting the environment, we will light up some needy’s life. \n\nWISHING YOU ALL A PROSPEROUS AND AN ECO-FRIENDLY DIWALI !!! ','Diwali - The festival of lights','','publish','open','open','','diwali-the-festival-of-lights','','','2014-10-23 16:41:11','2014-10-23 11:11:11','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1514',0,'post','',0),(1526,13,'2014-10-29 21:38:02','2014-10-29 16:08:02','<blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">“Dr. B.R. Ambedkar\'s passion for the abolition of Untouchability  and the eradication of caste is as relevant today as it was 75 years ago”</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a title=\"Dr. B.R. Ambedkar\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/B._R._Ambedkar\" target=\"_blank\">Dr. B.R. Ambedkar</a> explains the derivation of the caste system and how it has persisted. He then pleads that it is not viable to annihilate the caste system without annihilating the spiritual philosophy on which the organization is founded. Ambedkar not only criticizes the caste system for its cruel social array but he also presents a substitute social array based on egalitarianism, emancipation and sorority - egalitarianism.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Dr. Ambedkar stood firm and argued at length for his principles (equality, liberation and fraternity) whereas on conjectural level, the Indian Constitution envisages building a social array around. The Constitution de-recognizes caste based on social order and strives through a mixture of provisions to construct a caste-less social system. It prohibits discrimination in the public on the basis of gender, caste, religion, birth place or kind. It also lays down optimistic dealings for ameliorating of the social as well as economic conditions of the conventionally disadvantaged social groups so that they do not suffer caste based discrimination. In short, the Indian Republic plans to build a caste-less society.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Dr. Ambedkar was an intellectual man, always thinking in terms of humanizing the lots of millions in India. He took born in a lower caste family. He was kept isolated from top universities abroad even while being highly educated. One time his peon refused to bring him a glass of water as he belonged to a Mahar community. He has undergone humiliations at different point of his life but he didn’t have any hard feelings for anyone and also didn’t want to take revenge for all the agony and mortification he received. On the other hand, he tried his best to improve the obnoxious social practice in which he passed with a distinction.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/02sm_arundhati_jpg_1773723e.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1536\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/02sm_arundhati_jpg_1773723e.jpg\" alt=\"Annihilation of Caste \" width=\"318\" height=\"488\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In this context of a thorough bifurcation of caste from faith, the essential question in ”The Annihilation of Caste” relates social reform with political reform describing his contemporary environment; Ambedkar writes that platforms including the National Congress argued that political reform must lead social reform, whereas the Social Conference and the like insisted social change must be at the top of political change. Social reforms was finally defeated as the majority of the Hindu community remained apathetic to the unfair social circumstances within their midst and, instead, desperately focused\non finding liberation from British Rule.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">At first there are succession of letter screening the dialogue amid Dr. Ambedkar and other co-worker’s of Jat Pat Todak Mandal, in which connotation of annihilation of religion is not the equivalent thing in the views of Dr. Ambedkar and other common man. They desire to make Bhim their president. Jat pat Todak Mandal aim is to eradicate the caste system from the society for the welfare of the society. I totally agree with Dr. Ambedkar in this that this Mandal was uncongenial. The annual conference was postponed to mid-may.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Dr. B.R. Ambedkar emphasized on eradication of Hindu religious conviction so much that he even refer them as “sick men of India, and that their sickness is causing danger to the health and happiness of other Indians, to which he has my full support”. Due to this he made many enemies inside as well as outside the Mandal. He was told that the address is correct and he should order the printing of 1000 copies of his address. After the address was printed he was told address need’s editing and was back stabbed . Although he was forced to cut the last paragraph in his address in which he has talked about eradication of Hinduism from society, but he didn’t changed a thing. He agreed to cancel the conference but cannot allow printing of address in Toto. he didn’t waste the copies whereas he sold them to the general public so that they also can see Dr. Ambedkar point of view in relation to caste. Sale of the address took place in great numbers as a result the address was also translated into many languages like Marathi, Hindi, Punjabi and Malayalam. 1500 copies of English edition were sold within 2 months. Also various editions were published afterwards in which certain additions was seen. He surely has made many followers through this.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With annihilation of religion he also expressed his views on bringing down the whole caste system along with its causes, effects, ways and different problems they are going to face during the process. In order to bring down the whole caste system one has to destroy the religious ideas or the misconceptions that are in the mind of people. He focused on various problems that aroused through the caste. Along with caste he also focused on Untouchability. Untouchability plays the role of a catalyst in problem of caste in society.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hinduism is the oldest religion followed till date and is considered strong and unquestionable. The main drawback of Hinduism is the caste as it degrades it in many ways like fellow Hinduism won’t help his fellow Hinduism without knowing it’s caste, for example: a Brahmin would never help a , Kshatriya, Vaishya, or Shudra as they come at lower level in the hierarchy of caste in Hinduism, which is not the case in other religions as a result it is degrading the whole religion.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Dr. Ambedkar showed some ways to minimize the effect of caste system with inter- marriages and inter-dinning. Marriage is considered as sacred bond and if it is inter-caste then people of different caste will get to know each other and will understand with other, they will get to know that they are not different from each other. People also have a misconception between law and religion. They are not able to differentiate between law and religion, whereas there is no place of law (Rules and Regulations) in religion. At last I would end this review by saying that I am in full support of Dr. B.R. Ambedkar ideology he has shown in this article.</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">IN THE WORDS OF <a title=\"Arundhati Roy\" href=\"http://www.thehindu.com/books/literary-review/the-doctor-and-the-saint/article5740369.ece\" target=\"_blank\">ARUNDHATI ROY</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">“Annihilation of Caste is B.R. Ambedkar’s most radical text. It is not an argument directed at Hindu fundamentalists or extremists, but at those who considered themselves moderate, those whom Ambedkar called “the best of Hindus”— and some academics call “left-wing Hindus”. Ambedkar’s point is that to believe in the Hindu shastras and to simultaneously think of one as liberal or moderate is a contradiction in terms. When the text of Annihilation of Caste was published, the man who is often called the ‘Greatest of Hindus’ — Mahatma Gandhi responded to Ambedkar’s provocation.</p>\n</blockquote>','Annihilation of Caste by Dr. B.R. Ambedkar','','publish','open','open','','annihilation-caste-dr-b-r-ambedkar','','','2014-10-29 21:38:02','2014-10-29 16:08:02','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1526',0,'post','',0),(1536,2,'2014-10-29 15:09:07','2014-10-29 09:39:07','','02sm_Arundhati_jpg_1773723e','','inherit','open','open','','02sm_arundhati_jpg_1773723e','','','2014-10-29 15:09:07','2014-10-29 09:39:07','',1526,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/02sm_arundhati_jpg_1773723e.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1542,2,'2014-10-29 15:26:24','2014-10-29 09:56:24','','hqdefault','','inherit','open','open','','hqdefault','','','2014-10-29 15:26:24','2014-10-29 09:56:24','',1526,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/hqdefault.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1544,2,'2014-10-29 15:28:26','2014-10-29 09:58:26','','hqdefault','','inherit','open','open','','hqdefault-2','','','2014-10-29 15:28:26','2014-10-29 09:58:26','',1526,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/hqdefault1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1550,11,'2014-11-12 09:58:32','2014-11-12 04:28:32','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As it seems “Make-In-India” sounds great and we all hope that it results in the creation of many opportunities for the unemployed. Decent jobs will be created on a large scale in the manufacturing sector. But is this not delusional to some extent ?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As it seems “Make-In-India” sounds great and we all hope that it results in the creation of many opportunities for the unemployed. Decent jobs will be created on a large scale in the manufacturing sector. But is this not delusional to some extent ?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In short, Manufacturing is good.\nA fairly recent example of this transition is South Korea. During the 1950s manufacturing sector’s share was around 28% but since then it has fallen by 10 percentage points. Similarly China is considered to be the epitome of manufacturing but between 1950 and 2002, it had lost around 16 million jobs in this field.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Cons:\nManufacturing output will race ahead but without creating any of the jobs lost in that sector. Robots, automation and 3-D printers are minimizing human involvement. Due to global trade, Indian manufacturing would have to compete with the best and cheapest the world has to offer. So the Indian manufacturers would be compelled to use the latest technologies and production techniques and hence cut down the jobs.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Pros:\nWith a developing manufacturing sector a lot of service sector jobs would be created. Advertising Sales, transportation inputs and outputs, design, testing, after sales services etc. would be created.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Solution:\nSo if we want to sustain this technology driven era we need good quality education and healthcare, financial capacity, good infrastructure, good levels of social security and a functional governance.If these requirements are not met then due to global trade, countries like Singapore which give excellent manufacturing services would bag the opportunity and have a hold on a possible world’s largest manufacturing sector.\nNow it’s upon this government how they want to pursue this vision and make it a reality, that is for the people and by the people of INDIA.</p>','Make in India: A vision by our Prime Minister Narendra Modi','','publish','open','open','','make-india-vision-prime-minister-narendra-modi','','','2014-11-12 09:58:32','2014-11-12 04:28:32','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1550',0,'post','',0),(1558,9,'2014-11-03 13:43:32','2014-11-03 08:13:32','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/b.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1559\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/b.png\" alt=\"b\" width=\"259\" height=\"194\" /></a></p>\n&nbsp;\n\nWhenever the name ‘KASHMIR’ is heard by anyone, two main things passes through their mind.\n\nThe Beauty of the valley and its conflicts.\n\nKashmir, right from 1947 has been the Centre of problems between Hindustan and Pakistan.\n\nEven after knowing that Maharaja Hari Singh signed the agreement in the favour of Hindustan, Pakistan has been trying to capture the place from last 65 years in vain.\n\nProblems have always been in plethora in Kashmir Valley but even after unstable Government in J &amp; K and Confused orders from Central, our Indian Forces have managed to keep it safe from Pakis.\n\n<a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/n.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1560 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/n.png\" alt=\"n\" width=\"208\" height=\"243\" /></a>\n\nBut the reason(s) why Kashmir Valley is news nowadays are many.\n\nFirst of all, the Movie <strong>HAIDER. </strong>Yes, I don’t have anything against Shahid Kapoor or Vishal Bharadwaj but acting or making a film which condemns the efforts of Fauj in the border is definitely not done.\n\nI or You don’t have any authority or Right to comment on this highly sensitive topic, so here’s the link to the review of a Man, ‘who has been there and done that.’\n\n<a href=\"http://agniveer.com/a-soldier-reviews-haider/\"><strong>http://agniveer.com/a-soldier-reviews-haider/</strong></a>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\nBhutto, on snatching the Kashmir from our claws. Yea, although I have nothing personal against the Actor and Maker, I definitely hate this Ba*tard. His Mum was assassinated publicly and all he could do about this was ABSOLUTELY nothing and he dreams about taking Kashmir.\n\nNo doubt he was welcomed by the crowd in Kashmir with Eggs and Tomatoes. Bloody clot!\n\nWhenever I think of this person, all I can think of is this <strong>ONE QUOTE.</strong>\n\n<strong><em>‘ Hindustani, earth se mars pahoch gaya but Pakistani abhi tak Kashmir hi pahoch nai paye!’</em></strong>\n\nHindustan has been trying from last 10-15 years to increase the quality of Kashmiris life by introducing many Schemes, one of them is<em> AMAN KI AASHA.</em>\n\nBut until and unless , we don’t start respecting Kasmiris and start considering them Indians whole heartedly, all the schemes will go in vain.\n\nRemember, around 120 languages are spoken in India, still its world’s democracy. If our ancestors were able to hold the nation, weave the nation for 60-65 years..even we can .\n\n&nbsp;\n\nJai Hind !','KASHMIR ISSUE','','publish','open','open','','kashmir-issue','','','2014-11-03 13:43:32','2014-11-03 08:13:32','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1558',0,'post','',0),(1559,2,'2014-11-03 13:26:50','2014-11-03 07:56:50','','b','','inherit','open','open','','b','','','2014-11-03 13:26:50','2014-11-03 07:56:50','',1558,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/b.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1560,2,'2014-11-03 13:29:58','2014-11-03 07:59:58','','n','','inherit','open','open','','n','','','2014-11-03 13:29:58','2014-11-03 07:59:58','',1558,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/n.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1562,13,'2014-11-04 17:49:22','2014-11-04 12:19:22','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Why should we volunteer?</strong> I mean we are not paid after all the hard work we do for the institution. If you ask this to yourself then don’t worry, because you are perfectly normal. Everyone is rational and desires to work only for the enticement, then what in the world is the power that gets so many individuals interested in volunteering?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">“Volunteering is generally considered an altruistic activity and is intended to promote goodness or improve human quality of life. In return, this activity can produce a feeling of self-worth and respect”-technically speaking; but according to me volunteering is an activity which we do in order to satisfy our personal emotional needs.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There is no age of learning and there is no better teacher than experience. Volunteering helps you to experience different things in the world around you. When you work and get involved in an activity, you learn new things and how to manage those in a fraction of second. This power comes from within you. This kind of learning is what I call true learning, because unlike traditional methods you don’t read theories and apply them in real life but instead you learn it without any help. That sensation my friend is what I call true power of experience which you can’t get by reading stuff, but you have to do it in order to gain it. For example, Mr. Nighavar Rao was a math teacher and used to have lots of free time, so in order to fully utilize that time he started volunteering in which he taught blind students. He found it too difficult at the starting but he didn’t lose hope and finally got an idea how to teach the underprivileged children all by himself. Through this activity he learnt how to be patient and remain calm at moments. Also how to use various different resources in teaching. Volunteering has made him a better teacher now.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1567 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images.jpg\" alt=\"images\" width=\"257\" height=\"196\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Volunteering cannot only help you by gaining experience but also helps you to see things in your background or in society from a different point of view; also finally absorbing the reality of the world. For example, usually people see several children working on roads, small shops, pulling rickshaws but I want to ask you one question, i.e. what are the actions you have taken to stop it ? Many of you will have blank faces and may be some of you will proudly say that we did something and those who did something are nothing but the volunteers themselves. Many will be shocked if they knew the gravity and gruesome nature of human trafficking existing in the present world. When people volunteer in activities that involve the happiness of someone else, then an inner satisfaction is felt, and finally we get peace in our mind.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Personal satisfaction is the “greatest gift” volunteering can provide you. A sense of giving to society helps you to sleep well at night. Happiness is doing things for others and not asking a dime for that (volunteering). If you want to find peace  and long term happiness then service of others is the best way to go about it. Along with personal satisfaction volunteering also helps in medical ways. Scientists have proven that volunteering not only reduces stress but also make you healthier. Also Volunteering saves the resources of the society.  The estimated value of volunteer’s time is $15.39 per hour. So think that how much resources you are saving which can be used in some other places.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-13.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1566 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-13.jpg\" alt=\"images (1)\" width=\"299\" height=\"169\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As a volunteer one interacts with new faces, sometimes on a daily basis. When we meet new people and travel new places we create memories and share experiences, make new friends and enjoy the time with them. This journey  is just priceless for everyone and everyone wants it in some or the other way. Trust me when I say “Everyone wants to have a good time” and volunteering is a thing that helps you achieving a good time.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Besides the whole emotional thing joined with the volunteering there is also some fun part where we get opportunities to enjoy ourselves. There are institutions who send their volunteers to some tourist spots like Manali, for work; where they work for the welfare of the society but at the same time also have fun. For them it’s like putting cherry on a piece of cake and having double fun.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">“Helpiez “ is also one of the portal who is giving free cultural tourism package to Uttarakhand lofty mountains which includes living with villagers ,knowing their culture ,traditions and chance to record their marriage  rituals etc to  those volunteers who will complete 1000 points by doing social work and these experience you can’t but it from money but you can easily get it by doing social work.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-21.jpg\">\n</a><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-21.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1565\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-21.jpg\" alt=\"images (2)\" width=\"279\" height=\"183\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You can customize your search through this link according to your interest and region and get indulge in volunteering work</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">And I know volunteering is tiring, consumes up our time and also there is no monetary incentive but still I think that volunteering is just a good thing to do and duty of every citizen to try it, at least once.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>','Why should we do volunteering?','“Volunteering is generally considered an altruistic activity and is intended to promote goodness or improve human quality of life. In return, this activity can produce a feeling of self-worth and respect”-technically speaking; but according to me volunteering is an activity which we do in order to satisfy our personal needs involving lots of emotions for the activity.\n','publish','open','open','','volunteering','','','2014-11-04 17:49:22','2014-11-04 12:19:22','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1562',0,'post','',0),(1563,2,'2014-11-04 17:34:22','2014-11-04 12:04:22','','images (4)','','inherit','open','open','','images-4-2','','','2014-11-04 17:34:22','2014-11-04 12:04:22','',1562,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-41.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1564,2,'2014-11-04 17:34:28','2014-11-04 12:04:28','','images (3)','','inherit','open','open','','images-3-2','','','2014-11-04 17:34:28','2014-11-04 12:04:28','',1562,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-31.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1565,2,'2014-11-04 17:34:32','2014-11-04 12:04:32','','images (2)','','inherit','open','open','','images-2-2','','','2014-11-04 17:34:32','2014-11-04 12:04:32','',1562,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-21.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1566,2,'2014-11-04 17:34:37','2014-11-04 12:04:37','','images (1)','','inherit','open','open','','images-1-2','','','2014-11-04 17:34:37','2014-11-04 12:04:37','',1562,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-13.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1567,2,'2014-11-04 17:34:42','2014-11-04 12:04:42','','images','','inherit','open','open','','images','','','2014-11-04 17:34:42','2014-11-04 12:04:42','',1562,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1575,13,'2014-11-08 19:47:28','2014-11-08 14:17:28','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Being humans, helping is in our very genes and we help not because we have to, but because we want to. There is a feeling or sensation that resonates within us and motivates us to help. The general values that are passed on from generation to generation that affect the fellow human beings in a big way and clear their decision to whether help or not.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">People usually help because of three very basic reasons. Firstly, the help is provided because the helper knows that if he/she helps someone then the other owes him and has to pay this debt whenever helper is in need. Secondly, if someone of the own family is in need of the help then the motive changes. Helping our own kin is like helping ourselves only. Thirdly, in order to gain confidence of the people or to socialize with others help is normally the best way to interact with someone without any difficulty. The very nature of humans to help is a result of a naturally selected predisposition that is activated and influenced by cognitive and social processes.  In short, there are three motives for helping: our desires for mastery, concrete rewards, and connectedness with others.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Whenever we are in a bad mood we always think of a way to divert our minds from something that is disturbing us or pushing us towards depression. I would suggest you to start helping from that point onwards. Helping not only diverts our mind but also lightens our mood and makes us happy. This is a kind of emotional reward that we get by helping others.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images1.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1579 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images1.jpg\" alt=\"images\" width=\"220\" height=\"229\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">People help in order to show sympathy or compassion or sometimes tenderness which leads to altruistic behavior. By helping they show that they care for others. Helping provides a smooth way to show whether one cares or not. It helps people to get socialize easily in a strange place with new people.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I would like to put some light on altruism: “Altruism is motivated by a desire to benefit others. As a result, altruistic people always help, even when they can escape the stressful situation very easily.” They are seen with certain respect in the society. This is a very good habit and even though you are altruistic or not, one should at least try to help everyone in the neighborhood.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is a general seen that an individual will prefer to help that person whom he knows than to a complete stranger. People tends to help those whom they know and are familiar with. They don’t want to take the risk for a complete stranger. Hence, we can say that connectedness promotes helping. We help people from our own group more than people from the out-group. This is especially the case in collectivistic cultures.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sometimes there are surprises behind the help. For example: one day on a sunny day I helped an old woman to cross the road and when I was going for my work, she called me from behind and gave me a packet of biscuit as a reward for my help. Helping sometimes can give you rewards also.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images.png\"><img class=\" wp-image-1580 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images.png\" alt=\"images\" width=\"189\" height=\"267\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In newspapers we see lots of missing person’s photographs and contact numbers given below in order to give any information if possible of the missing. If we help them finding the los then money is given to the informer. So we can say that there are monetary benefits of helping also.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">People now a days are more selfish and the feeling of helping is lost somewhere in the crowd. There are various social groups in the society and everyone wants that their group to be best, so they use the limited resources of the society all by themselves and don’t leave it for others or even left for replenishment of that resource. This promote self-interest. Which is wrong but this promotes more and more helping inside the group and development of the society where strong group would lead.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Help may be motivated by perceived rewards for the helper, or deterred by perceived costs or risks. These rewards and risks can be emotional: people sometimes help to alleviate their own distress at the victim\'s suffering, reflecting egoism. People are often motivated by a feeling of empathy to relieve another\'s suffering, reflecting altruism, because it is not motivated by even indirect or emotional rewards for the helper. In a social dilemma, rewards for each individual are in direct conflict with what is best for the group. However, people can be motivated by feelings of group connectedness to act for the good of the group. When group identification increases commitment to shared goals and norms, social dilemmas can be successfully resolved.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Along with these there are many more reasons to help but helping doesn’t need any reason or motive it comes from within us. True help is something that emerges from our heart and soul.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The rewards and benefits aside, I think being helpful and kind is in the very nature of human beings. Man is often regarded as a social animal. We live in a society-in harmony with fellow humans. The feeling of service and kindness to others is always there in us, what differs from person to person is who/what is at the receiving end of this kindness. As you pointed out correctly that there can be many incentives before a person to be helpful to others, but the goal in life should be to be of service to others without looking for a personal benefit. Because it is this service that is a path to achieve long term happiness in life. We often mistake materialistic gains/pleasures in life for true happiness, but happiness is only real and meaningful when one can share it with another person by doing well for him/her. And there is no small way to do an act of kindness, one could simply start by greeting people with a smile each day.</p>','Why should we help?','','publish','open','open','','help','','','2014-11-08 19:47:28','2014-11-08 14:17:28','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1575',0,'post','',1),(1577,2,'2014-11-08 19:50:17','2014-11-08 14:20:17','','images (1)','','inherit','open','open','','images-1-3','','','2014-11-08 19:50:17','2014-11-08 14:20:17','',1575,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-111.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1579,2,'2014-11-08 19:50:48','2014-11-08 14:20:48','','images','','inherit','open','open','','images-10','','','2014-11-08 19:50:48','2014-11-08 14:20:48','',1575,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1580,2,'2014-11-08 19:51:29','2014-11-08 14:21:29','','images','','inherit','open','open','','images-13','','','2014-11-08 19:51:29','2014-11-08 14:21:29','',1575,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1590,2,'2014-11-12 09:58:07','2014-11-12 04:28:07','','MAke in India','','inherit','open','open','','13','','','2014-11-12 09:58:07','2014-11-12 04:28:07','',1550,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/13.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1618,13,'2014-11-19 10:38:51','2014-11-19 05:08:51','&nbsp;\n\nBesides all the expensive gifts you can afford why I want you take a part out of your income and donate is:\n\n&nbsp;\n<ul>\n	<li>Donations are tax deductible</li>\n</ul>\nYes! This is one of the benefits of donation but according to me this shouldn’t be the reason for donation. Donation is noble cause and in order to promote it government has taken this initiative. Not only the donation but all the expenses which are not reimbursed in a noble cause are subject to tax deduction.\n<ul>\n	<li>Giving to charity may improve your sense of well-being</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\nMany people doing their job and following their daily routine thinks that they are living their lives but it is just the lie, instead they are just spending their time. After donation many people find a new purpose in life and improve the way you think of others and society.\n<a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/donation.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1621 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/donation.jpg\" alt=\"donation\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>\n<ul>\n	<li>Supporting a cause can help keep you informed about issues of social injustice</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\nWhen considering donating to a charity, many people tend to research the issues connected to that organization. As a result, you become more educated about social injustices around the world. You may discover new points of view and opinions on topics about which you were previously uniformed. By this you become more and more socially aware about social things prevailing in our society. We can say that donation helps you getting aware about the issues of society.\n\n&nbsp;\n<ul>\n	<li>Giving to charity out of spiritual conviction can strengthen your spiritual life</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\nSelfless giving is a key component to many spiritual and religious belief systems. There are many institutions like the art of living, who tell us about inner peace and satisfaction. I can guarantee you that by donation you will not only attain satisfaction but also you will feel good after it.\n\n&nbsp;\n<ul>\n	<li>Volunteering with a charity may result in physical and social benefits</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\nAfter donating financially to a charity or non-profit organization, you may feel an inner pull to become more involved with the cause by donating your time and skill as well. By volunteering, you have the opportunity to build your social circles while reaping the physical, mental and spiritual benefits from the labor you contribute to your favorite cause.\n\n<a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/make-a-donation-hi.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1620 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/make-a-donation-hi.png\" alt=\"make-a-donation-hi\" width=\"600\" height=\"192\" /></a>','Why should we donate  ?','','publish','open','open','','donate','','','2014-11-19 10:38:51','2014-11-19 05:08:51','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1618',0,'post','',0),(1619,2,'2014-11-19 10:32:14','2014-11-19 05:02:14','','where_donate_ad_sav','','inherit','open','open','','where_donate_ad_sav','','','2014-11-19 10:32:14','2014-11-19 05:02:14','',1618,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/where_donate_ad_sav.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1620,2,'2014-11-19 10:32:57','2014-11-19 05:02:57','','make-a-donation-hi','','inherit','open','open','','make-a-donation-hi','','','2014-11-19 10:32:57','2014-11-19 05:02:57','',1618,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/make-a-donation-hi.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1621,2,'2014-11-19 10:33:12','2014-11-19 05:03:12','','donation','','inherit','open','open','','donation','','','2014-11-19 10:33:12','2014-11-19 05:03:12','',1618,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/donation.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1631,14,'2014-11-20 23:26:38','2014-11-20 17:56:38','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">            \"Children are the most precious beings gifted by God to Parents\"</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">But what if the children are left by their parents itself ? Imagination itself scares right?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Yes, it is really a heart breaking thing for everyone who have  tendency to respond to these abandoned and orphan children.\nOnce if we look at their STRUGGLE, I am sure our heart will go on melting. Their life is very complicated from their childhood stage itself and they have to support their livelihood all by themselves. Each and every day they face many challenges which throw lots of burden to their tiny little lives.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Here\'s a pathetic situation which i have witnessed.\nI wish this could be an EYEOPENER to the people who doesn\'t care about all this stuff\nThis is the story of a child which i have personally encountered with, the tale goes as follows....\nDuring my schooling when I was about to leave my school that last year of my SSC our school management has planned for a visit to an ORPHANAGE .Finally the day came and we were there. All our classmates took many eatables, books, money for them and we ourselves distributed all this stuff among them.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We sang songs , we danced for few numbers to provide them with little entertainment.\nInterestingly they were utterly happy, frankly speaking they were overwhelmed for what all we have done to them...they thanked us too many times and told us that we can\'t forget this day in our lifetime.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/3.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1634 \" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/3.png\" alt=\"3\" width=\"316\" height=\"237\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We spent lot of time by talking with them knowing their whereabouts etc.. .suddenly i saw a girl who was standing behind the door and staring at each one around and she was a bit tensed to mingle with everyone there. Noticing that i went near to hear and started speaking to her for few seconds she spoke nothing only silence ran between us...then i stopped talking and i too started to stare at her as she did.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Then she herself started speaking by introducing herself our conversation went on and she told few rhymes stories. An interesting aspect about her is she have a very good memory that she knew each and every capital of states and countries at the age of 7.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> I was really astonished to listen all those from her...she even said few jokes and we both giggled and had fun too. And then a question struck my mind is that how was she there...the very next minute i asked her who brought you here?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">That answer what i heard made me DUMBSTRUCK she replied that \"my MOTHER left me here and she asked me to stay here and she will return after a while and take me home\"</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> But the BITTER TRUTH is that she  is  NEVER BACK\nThat little girl\'s eyes turned WET when she narrated me this incident</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/41.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1635\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/41.jpg\" alt=\"4\" width=\"365\" height=\"243\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">   I was speechless for a moment.\nNone of them knew the reason why she left her own child there....Many similar stories we encounter in our daily routine. But the fact is that only FEW of us Bother and respond ,some of them STARE ,and some of them IGNORE!!!\nGenerally whenever we were struck with a hectic problem and was tensed about the situations at that particular moment when we tend to see a beautiful smile of child certainly there will a glow on our face at that moment we even forget those problems.\nTHEY are the ones who can turn everything colourful  and spread happiness around.\nBut these little innocent children without their involvement they are leading a lonely life ..many of them don\'t even have their primary needs..throughout their life they only strive for feeding their stomach</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">They have none to share their feelings ,none to care for them...many of them have a great potential and deep passion to study but they can\'t ...only few of them have supporting hands to build up their future but what about the rest of them?!\nSurprisingly some of us go on criticise and interfere  in their lives. and start naming them as ORPHANS ,CURSED children etc.., This brings a negative impact over them and they start behaving rude towards the society.\nAnd the RAW TRUTH is that these kind of things happen and these children are left alone only due to some hasty DECISIONS made by their parents and family members.\nThe ROOT REASONS  for these issues are POVERTY and PRE-MARITAL SEX. These things alone make their life so miserable this we can observe in our society in a crystal clear way.</p>\nThis surely needs a strong solution which lies within ourselves. We YOUTH can bring a DRASTIC CHANGE. This can be just done by just raising our VOICE AGAINST these issues and also by CREATING AWARENESS .So that it could be a proud factor as we are the STARTERS for this ENTHRALLING EVENT.<a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/7.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1638 \" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/7.jpg\" alt=\"7\" width=\"591\" height=\"414\" /></a>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">All that they need is a CARING HEART and HELPING HANDS. And a well known FACT is that when a SEED sown gives us FRUITS only after a certain period of TIME. So let’s SOW a SEED first and STEP ahead to SET a PATH for the BETTER FUTURE.</p>\nHereby i would like to share my ideas which may bring out a change when followed...spending MONEY WISELY...AVOIDING the WASTAGE of FOOD...DONATING our CLOTHES ,BOOKS etc so that it might be a contribution from our part hope this might work out better.\n\n\"  <em>AT FIRST IT MAY BE A MOVEMENT WITH MINUTE MOTION  &amp; who KNOWS LATER IT MIGHT BE A REVOLUTION\"</em>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>.</em></p>','I was born ORPHAN !!!','','publish','open','open','','born-orphan','','','2014-11-20 23:26:38','2014-11-20 17:56:38','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1631',0,'post','',5),(1633,2,'2014-11-20 22:47:26','2014-11-20 17:17:26','','2','','inherit','open','open','','2','','','2014-11-20 22:47:26','2014-11-20 17:17:26','',1631,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1634,2,'2014-11-20 22:47:31','2014-11-20 17:17:31','','3','','inherit','open','open','','3','','','2014-11-20 22:47:31','2014-11-20 17:17:31','',1631,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/3.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1635,2,'2014-11-20 22:47:36','2014-11-20 17:17:36','','4','','inherit','open','open','','4-2','','','2014-11-20 22:47:36','2014-11-20 17:17:36','',1631,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/41.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1636,2,'2014-11-20 22:47:41','2014-11-20 17:17:41','','5','','inherit','open','open','','5','','','2014-11-20 22:47:41','2014-11-20 17:17:41','',1631,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/5.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1637,2,'2014-11-20 22:47:45','2014-11-20 17:17:45','','6','','inherit','open','open','','6','','','2014-11-20 22:47:45','2014-11-20 17:17:45','',1631,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/6.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1638,2,'2014-11-20 22:47:50','2014-11-20 17:17:50','','7','','inherit','open','open','','7','','','2014-11-20 22:47:50','2014-11-20 17:17:50','',1631,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/7.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1639,2,'2014-11-20 22:50:35','2014-11-20 17:20:35','','1','','inherit','open','open','','1','','','2014-11-20 22:50:35','2014-11-20 17:20:35','',1631,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1641,2,'2014-11-20 22:54:52','2014-11-20 17:24:52','','lonley girl spread_opt','','inherit','open','open','','lonley-girl-spread_opt','','','2014-11-20 22:54:52','2014-11-20 17:24:52','',1631,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/lonley-girl-spread_opt.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1649,10,'2014-11-21 01:00:03','2014-11-20 19:30:03','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">My parents often ask me not to eat outside food, eat before sunset, don’t watch TV or speak while eating and many more things. I would hardly understand the importance of these things and question all of these, but then these things seem to have a logic.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Food is defined on the basis of its calorific value and the various constituents. But these measurements do not actually seem to work, as people eating same food have diverse physique and health conditions. There must be something which is not being taken into account.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Let’s try to find that missing something. The whole process of eating has 2 basic aspects – food and us. For simplicity, let us assume that everything is a wave. Here we have two waves – the human-wave and the food-wave. Now when these two waves meet, they may have constructive, destructive or partial interference.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As we eat food, our body receives it. As this process occurs, the wave interference takes place. We need to ensure that a constructive interference takes place-that is the condition where the maximum utilization of the food takes place. Does this depend only on the kind of food we eat or can we also affect this wave interference and if we can then how? The answer lies in many old texts which talk about Ayurveda and food systems like the Charak-Samhita.  They say that we must eat our food with hands, paying proper attention to the act of eating, chewing properly, with proper posture etc. These are in-fact ways to align ourselves-that is to prepare body-wave to receive the food-wave. If we don’t put attention to the food as we eat it, we receive it physically, but not the way it is required. The food-wave goes out of phase with our body wave, and we do now utilize a lot of nutrients it has to offer.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-211.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1656 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-211.jpg\" alt=\"images (2)\" width=\"237\" height=\"213\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Take chapatti in your hands, break it and while dipping it in the daal and sabji feel the warmth of it on the fingers and bring that piece of food closely observing its texture and the scent and kiss the tips of your fingers with the lips as you take in the food. Chew it slowly feeling the food in your mouth with the tongue and sallow it down. Don’t be in a hurry to get the next piece of chapatti. Enjoy each bit and the food will die to shed all its nutrients to your body.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To understand food-wave let us start from the plants and trees. Medieval texts say that plants must be grown in proper sunlight and open environment and those fruits and vegetables must be preferred which have fallen than those which are plucked while attached to the plant. It has been recently studied that plants do feel pain. Plants would obviously not be happy giving away fruit you snatched from it causing pain to it. It’s same as tearing away your hair and nails forcefully by your friend.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Now as we have got the raw material, let’s come to cooking. We know that mother’s food is better than hotel food or mess food. But is it really true only because mother cooks food with cleanliness choosing healthy vegetables or is there something more than this attributed to the mother. There is in-fact something else which is more important than just cleanliness. It’s the mentality of the cook while cooking. A chef in a restaurant considers food a profit making commodity and nothing else. He may put all his efforts to ensure hygiene, but only a mother fills the food with her love and care. She desires to keep her child fit and energetic and wishes to see him successful and happy. She wants the food-wave to amplify to the maximum extent possible and align in the way suitable for the child’s body-wave.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Now for simple analogy let’s again take 2 parameters of the wave-amplitude and alignment. The body-wave doesn’t change much in terms of amplitude as its vast compared to food-wave’s amplitude. Then what is left is the alignment of body-wave. And this is where all our dos and don’ts come into picture. In case of food-wave, amplitude depends on calorific value, composition and mode of cooking, but alignment depends on role of nature and mentality of cook among other things. This whole set of parameters determining alignment and amplitude has been collectively coined into a new term “<strong>Pranik Value</strong>”.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-411.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1659 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-411.jpg\" alt=\"images (4)\" width=\"228\" height=\"221\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Pranik value is something which cannot be easily defined. It is something like health of food, not only in terms of quality or the amount of nutrients present. The food prepared by your mother has greater Pranik value because the former one had a touch of mother’s love, despite the fact that in both cases same food was prepared with same method. Plants better exposed to sunlight and air have a nature’s touch. Similarly, open cooking makes better food compared to microwave or pressure cooker, because nature has an opportunity to interfere in the former. Pranik value is not just a property of food, but it also depends on us- the way we eat food, the thoughts in our mind while eating food and the activities we do after eating food.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If we drink water or juice or tea after food, they suppress the digestive juices in our stomach and the food would not be utilized properly.  Actually we are decreasing the Pranik value of the food we just ate. Food with same calorific value would respond differently depending on these. Thus Pranik value is a function of the whole ingestion-excretion process.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Even prayers before food have a dual effect of making the food more eatable and our body more receivable. “Prasad” given in temples has a very high Pranik value, as it is prepared by the devotees with extreme devotion to God and even a small amount is sufficient for the day. Even if nothing like God exists, Prasad would still work for anyone who believes in the supremacy of someone who is the symbol of good.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It all comes out to a point where we could say that food has got a soul of its own. If we criticize the mess food while eating it, we are doing no different than eating waste as the arrogance in food doesn’t let it surrender so easily. The process of eating is no different than making love. Human and food are the two partners desperately wanting to mate. But even if one of the partners is in no mood, the process turns into a rape. The way we treat food is not different than raping it. There has to be the love all throughout before, during and after eating same as there is in making love.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-121.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1660\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-121.jpg\" alt=\"images (1)\" width=\"275\" height=\"183\" /></a></p>','Human-Food Duality','','publish','open','open','','human-food-duality','','','2014-11-21 01:00:03','2014-11-20 19:30:03','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1649',0,'post','',0),(1650,2,'2014-11-21 00:58:33','2014-11-20 19:28:33','','images','','inherit','open','open','','images-15','','','2014-11-21 00:58:33','2014-11-20 19:28:33','',1649,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1656,2,'2014-11-21 17:49:52','2014-11-21 12:19:52','','images (2)','','inherit','open','open','','images-2-3','','','2014-11-21 17:49:52','2014-11-21 12:19:52','',1649,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-211.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1658,2,'2014-11-21 17:52:40','2014-11-21 12:22:40','','images (3)','','inherit','open','open','','images-3-3','','','2014-11-21 17:52:40','2014-11-21 12:22:40','',1649,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-311.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1659,2,'2014-11-21 17:52:47','2014-11-21 12:22:47','','images (4)','','inherit','open','open','','images-4-3','','','2014-11-21 17:52:47','2014-11-21 12:22:47','',1649,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-411.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1660,2,'2014-11-21 17:52:59','2014-11-21 12:22:59','','images (1)','','inherit','open','open','','images-1-4','','','2014-11-21 17:52:59','2014-11-21 12:22:59','',1649,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-121.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1661,2,'2014-11-21 17:55:05','2014-11-21 12:25:05','','mono-food-eating-combination4','','inherit','open','open','','mono-food-eating-combination4','','','2014-11-21 17:55:05','2014-11-21 12:25:05','',1649,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/mono-food-eating-combination4.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1665,18,'2014-11-21 18:48:36','2014-11-21 13:18:36','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">People are afraid of adversities. They shun difficulties and want to lead a life of luxury and comfort. But the world famous poet-dramatist, Shakespeare, held a different opinion. For him the use of adversity is sweet. He compares adversity to toads. A toad is ugly and poisonous. We hate it. But it has a jewel in its head. So also we afraid of adversity, but it has also many sweet uses. Adversity is a blessing in disguise. It is not a cure as is generally supposed. Misfortunes make a man. They are the real tests of character. One who faces difficulties comes out of the encounter better and abler. They are like a hard school master. Students are afraid of such a teacher. He takes work from them and punishes them, but he has the good of the students at heart. He makes their career. So also difficulties are good for a man in the long run.He should not be afraid of them.</p>\n<a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-61.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1666 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-61.jpg\" alt=\"images (6)\" width=\"217\" height=\"232\" /></a>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Difficulties train and develop the natural faculties of a man. Just as herbs give out their sweet fragrance when they are crushed, so a man of real ability or virtue shines all the brighter when pressed with difficulties. So we should not afraid of difficulties but rather welcome them. They are like the bitter pills which the doctor gives his patent to cure them. Adversity is to our own good. It may be bitter at the time but its uses are really sweet. Difficulties are the ladder on which we climb to success. Nothing great can be achieved or has been achieved, without grappling with difficulties. All the greatest man of the world is those who faced difficulties bravely and then overcame them. Those who lead a life of ease and comfort can never achieve much. Nothing s to be expected of such people but every thing is possible for those who have faced difficulties have failed but have persisted in spite of failure. Difficulties vanish when they are faced boldly. They are like thieves that take to their heals at the first encounter. What appear to be insurmountable mountains disappear before a bold attempt and paths hitherto unseen open out to the view. Everest was conquered by those who boldly faced the dangers in their way and did not falter in their attempt, in spite of initial failure. Columbus could discover America only because he faced the unknown oceans with confidence and did not care for any difficulties. All human civilization is but a record of the exploits of these heroic souls who were undeterred by any difficulties that came in their way. Rather, the difficulties were but spurs that goaded them on to make yet greater efforts.</p>\n <a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-51.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-1667 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-51.jpg\" alt=\"images (5)\" width=\"393\" height=\"145\" /></a>','Misfortune a Blessing in Disguise','','publish','open','open','','misfortune-blessing-disguise','','','2014-11-21 18:48:36','2014-11-21 13:18:36','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1665',0,'post','',7),(1666,2,'2014-11-21 18:42:35','2014-11-21 13:12:35','','images (6)','','inherit','open','open','','images-6-2','','','2014-11-21 18:42:35','2014-11-21 13:12:35','',1665,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-61.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1667,2,'2014-11-21 18:42:43','2014-11-21 13:12:43','','images (5)','','inherit','open','open','','images-5-2','','','2014-11-21 18:42:43','2014-11-21 13:12:43','',1665,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-51.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1668,2,'2014-11-21 18:42:51','2014-11-21 13:12:51','??????????????????????','the-longer-we-dwell-on-our-misfortunes-1920x1080-inspirational-quote-wallpaper-432-2814654801','','inherit','open','open','','the-longer-we-dwell-on-our-misfortunes-1920x1080-inspirational-quote-wallpaper-432-2814654801','','','2014-11-21 18:42:51','2014-11-21 13:12:51','',1665,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/the-longer-we-dwell-on-our-misfortunes-1920x1080-inspirational-quote-wallpaper-432-2814654801.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1672,16,'2014-11-21 19:03:31','2014-11-21 13:33:31','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A new poll in France says 7 out of 10 people think Microsoft did more to change the world than the closest rival Apple. I think we would have similar results in other countries, if only because a lot more people (still!) use Microsoft products than Apple products, at least for personal computing which is (still!) the most important part of computing. So to say anything about a product we must compare to its closest rival and in this context undoubtedly Apple is the closest rival of Microsoft.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\nAlthough the Windows platform is still Microsoft’s bread and butter, the company has a wide range of products for both business intelligence and business integration.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It\'s hard to see a mention of Steve Jobs without the worlds \"change the world\" or \"changing an industry.\" And let\'s give him his due. Let\'s give him his due as one of the greatest entrepreneurs in history, as an amazing entrepreneur and visionary who left many \"dents\" in the universe. And he did change many industries, like music, film, and yes, personal computing.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">But in terms of sheer impact on the world? Microsoft wins, hands down.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Microsoft gave the world two things:</p>\n\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<li>Microsoft was the first real software company.</li>\n	<li>Microsoft did put a PC on every desk and in every home.</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">At the end of the day, it\'s that last part that matters. By shifting the value in computing to software, Microsoft commoditized computing hardware and made computing accessible to the masses. If this isn\'t one of the most significant events in history, nothing is.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Now, some people will say that Microsoft did this by copying Apple\'s innovations like the graphical user interface. Whatever. First of all, Apple famously copied those from Apple PARC. Great artists steal. Second of all, by any meaning of the word, the person who changes the world isn\'t the one who comes up with the idea, it\'s the one who executes on it, and 1980s Apple failed to execute</p>\n<a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/download-13.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1674 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/download-13.jpg\" alt=\"download (1)\" width=\"276\" height=\"183\" /></a>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Microsoft, being a software company, built an operating system platform that let thousands of others innovate which, along with Moore\'s Law, made PCs cheaper and more valuable every year which meant more and more people could get access to them, in a vicious circle.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Being the first big, viable software company also meant Microsoft cleared the way for thousands of other software innovators, when it was in no way obvious at the start that a company could be viable making just software.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The hardware may have been ugly, and the software clunky (a big reason why Windows is buggy is because of Microsoft\'s amazing 20 year commitment to backwards compatibility, which makes PC software a cohesive environment, a tremendous service to users and the world, for which it gets no credit.), but it was the software that millions of people used, and loved.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The mobile computing revolution, with smartphones and tablets, will be at least as big as the desktop computing revolution, and Apple is seriously taking the lead. Android has a good chance of disrupting iOS, but Apple also has a great chance of remaining the dominant mobile platform. Maybe 20 years from now we\'ll look back and see Apple had an impact at least as big as Microsoft in the 1980s.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">But if we\'re looking now, Microsoft clearly had a bigger impact on the world. The fact that we all love Apple products and they\'re gorgeous doesn\'t change the fact that the company that actually made the world realize the magic of software, and made computing accessible to almost everyone on the planet, is Microsoft.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">How to contribute to current trend of Microsoft : :</p>\n\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n	<li>Increasing its market share in mobile computing</li>\n	<li>Reduce the price of SQL servers</li>\n	<li>Incubate the number of young developers</li>\n	<li>Increase the share in automation department</li>\n	<li>Reduce the number of bugs (certainly affects the status of MICROSOFT</li>\n</ul>\n<a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-71.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1675 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-71.jpg\" alt=\"images (7)\" width=\"383\" height=\"131\" /></a>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>','IMPACT OF MICROSOFT ON THE WORLD','','publish','open','open','','impact-microsoft-world','','','2014-11-21 19:03:31','2014-11-21 13:33:31','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1672',0,'post','',0),(1673,2,'2014-11-21 18:58:17','2014-11-21 13:28:17','','Microsoft_Logo','','inherit','open','open','','microsoft_logo','','','2014-11-21 18:58:17','2014-11-21 13:28:17','',1672,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/microsoft_logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1674,2,'2014-11-21 19:00:36','2014-11-21 13:30:36','','download (1)','','inherit','open','open','','download-1-3','','','2014-11-21 19:00:36','2014-11-21 13:30:36','',1672,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/download-13.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1675,2,'2014-11-21 19:00:42','2014-11-21 13:30:42','','images (7)','','inherit','open','open','','images-7-2','','','2014-11-21 19:00:42','2014-11-21 13:30:42','',1672,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-71.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1678,17,'2014-11-21 19:25:38','2014-11-21 13:55:38','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Cleaning up the country cannot be the sole responsibility of sweepers. Do citizens have no role in this? We have to change this mindset.</em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>                                                                                                                        ~Narendra Modi</em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em> </em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">On 2<sup>nd</sup> Oct 2014 when the Prime Minister of India, Narendra Modi launched the ‘Swachh Bharat Abhiyaan’ a.k.a the ‘Clean India Movement’, there were both applauses and criticisms about it. Although reactions like these are expected after any big step is taken, the thing that these appraisers as well as critics should think about is the reason as to why the government of a country, which had been independent for the past 67 years, had to take such a drastic measure.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Cleanliness is something that should come to someone as naturally as breathing. No one likes being surrounded by filth. A clean environment is something which is in the wish list of every individual. Then why is it that India is never clean? Why is India portrayed as a filthy nation in the international movies?</p>\n<a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/o.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1679 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/o.jpg\" alt=\"o\" width=\"400\" height=\"250\" /></a>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As the quote by Mr.Narendra Modi rightly points out, no movement, no revolution can be successful unless and until the mass towards whom this movement is directed bring about a radical change in their mindset. Unless people realize that the dedication with which they strive to keep their houses shining and clean, the same dedication is needed to keep the surroundings of their houses clean too, the dream of a clean India by 2019 will remain a dream forever. A small start is all that is needed.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A group of anonymous altruists under the pseudonym of ‘The Ugly Indian’ have started a campaign in Bangalore wherein they don’t wait for the authorities to start the cleaning of their colonies and neighborhood. They kick start the process and in turn inspire others to do so. Measures like those are no doubt worthy of appreciation. But the real success of such initiatives are felt when the awareness these people are trying to spread, actually spread to the larger mass, affects their psyche and inspires them to follow in the good footsteps.</p>\n <a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/bn.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1681 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/bn.jpg\" alt=\"bn\" width=\"716\" height=\"420\" /></a><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/ui.jpg\">\n</a>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The GOI has launched the ‘Baal Swacchta Mission’ with an aim of spreading the awareness of cleanliness among the children. I think a ‘Yuva Swachhta Mission’ should also be in the pipeline. When students are taught of cleanliness and hygiene in the curriculum through subjects like moral science, why is there a need to launch a separate campaign for that? The answer goes back to the same old story – changing the mindset.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I had gone to the Barabati Stadium at Katak for the first ODI of India vs Srilanka recently. The stadium has a capacity of 45,000 and considering that at least 30,000 of the spectators must have visited the washrooms during the whole course of the match, the washrooms were so dirty by the time the match ended that it must have taken at least a couple of hours for the cleaning staffs to clean the mess the next day. Given the fact there was a school which was using the same washrooms, what message did we pass on to the kids when they came to school the next day?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Children will learn what they will see their elders doing. The moral science classes need to be taken up by the parents, grandparents and elder brothers and sisters.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As long as we keep on thinking ‘Yeh India hai..yahan sab kuch chalta hai’ and throw the packet of chips on the side of the road only with the excuse that there is no dustbin nearby, campaigns like “Swachh Bharat’ and ‘Ganga Bachao’ won’t be successful.</p>','SWACHH BHARAT ABHIYAAN','','publish','open','open','','swachh-bharat-abhiyaan','','','2014-11-21 19:25:38','2014-11-21 13:55:38','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1678',0,'post','',0),(1679,2,'2014-11-21 19:11:42','2014-11-21 13:41:42','','o','','inherit','open','open','','o','','','2014-11-21 19:11:42','2014-11-21 13:41:42','',1678,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/o.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1680,2,'2014-11-21 19:12:32','2014-11-21 13:42:32','','ui','','inherit','open','open','','ui','','','2014-11-21 19:12:32','2014-11-21 13:42:32','',1678,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/ui.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1681,2,'2014-11-21 19:14:24','2014-11-21 13:44:24','','bn','','inherit','open','open','','bn','','','2014-11-21 19:14:24','2014-11-21 13:44:24','',1678,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/bn.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1685,17,'2014-11-21 19:36:38','2014-11-21 14:06:38','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>As a leader, I am tough on myself and I raise the standard for everybody; however, I am very caring because I want people to excel at what they are doing so that they can aspire to be me in the future.</em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>                                                                                                                                    ~Indra Nooyi</em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em> </em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In today’s world where women like Indra Nooyi, Chanda Kochhar, Arundhati Bhattacharya or Marissa Mayer hold the top positions in their respective companies and are extremely efficient in their jobs, a topic like this seems ironic. However, contrary to that feeling, this topic is very much relevant in today’s corporate scenario.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Researches are still on as to decide who among the two – men or women, make better managers. The need for such researches arise because of the fact they men and women are still considered as two separate entities in the corporate world. Had the wall disappeared, research topics like those would have become obsolete.</p>\n <a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/cv.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1686 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/cv.jpg\" alt=\"cv\" width=\"428\" height=\"309\" /></a>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The fault however, doesn’t lie completely with the male dominated corporate scene. I agree there are certain situations to which the ladies succumb to and hence get stuck beneath the glass ceiling – situations like the chances of getting married in the next 6 months etc. I have personally seen situations where a girl is ruled out from the list of potential promotion winners only because she just got 26 years old and there are high chances that her parents might be thinking of getting her married real soon. My question is who gave them the idea? I don’t think either the girl or her parents would have done that. Then who did? Our centuries old cultures did. These cultures are so deep rooted in our minds that at a time when we have adopted at least 80% of the western work culture in our corporate offices (including referring to someone as old as your father by his first name) we are still bound by those shackles which ultimately slows down the progress of the whole nation.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Also there are instances when the girls have a preconceived notion that they won’t be able to break the glass ceiling and hence never attempt for it. And when ladies like Ursula Burns take charge and redirect the photocopying business to whole new dimensions, all they can do is praise her fortune and her courage.</p>\n <a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/vc.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1687 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/vc.jpg\" alt=\"vc\" width=\"270\" height=\"187\" /></a>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If we girls, after entering the corporate world, want to look up to someone to be inspired, there are hundreds of these successful ladies with even more successful winning stories, from whom we can get the inspiration we want. But the story doesn’t end here. The onus lies upon us to capitalize on their experiences, to aspire to perform and break through that glass ceiling, to set an example our juniors can refer to. We ourselves need to stop thinking of us as something different from the boys. There is no competition here. No one has asked us to perform better than the boys. We just need to make sure that although we might not be matching with their shoulders physically, but our work, commitment and dedication does! Let our performance do the talking.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Let’s bring in the change in our way of thinking and let’s make topics like ‘Are women better managers than men’ a research topic of history and not behavioral science.</p>','BREAKING THE GLASS CEILING – WOMEN IN THE CORPORATE WORLD','','publish','open','open','','breaking-glass-ceiling-women-corporate-world','','','2014-11-21 19:36:38','2014-11-21 14:06:38','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1685',0,'post','',0),(1686,2,'2014-11-21 19:31:44','2014-11-21 14:01:44','','cv','','inherit','open','open','','cv','','','2014-11-21 19:31:44','2014-11-21 14:01:44','',1685,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/cv.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1687,2,'2014-11-21 19:32:31','2014-11-21 14:02:31','','vc','','inherit','open','open','','vc','','','2014-11-21 19:32:31','2014-11-21 14:02:31','',1685,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/vc.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1688,2,'2014-11-21 19:34:48','2014-11-21 14:04:48','','women-empowerment-quotes-hd-wallpaper-17','','inherit','open','open','','women-empowerment-quotes-hd-wallpaper-17','','','2014-11-21 19:34:48','2014-11-21 14:04:48','',1685,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/women-empowerment-quotes-hd-wallpaper-17.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1690,17,'2014-11-21 19:47:04','2014-11-21 14:17:04','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Hold my hand and walk with me, we must break the back of social inequity;</em><em>We must empower every individual with a disability</em><em>, </em><em>to live with dignity in an inclusive society.</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>                                                                                                       ~William E. Lightbourne</em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Until a few years back, in a conservative societal structure like that in India, thinking of crossing the line of ‘acceptable social norms’ was considered a crime more heinous than murder. Thanks to the positive waves of education, technological developments and westernization that the mindset of the people of India is gradually broadening. People are gaining the courage of following their passions and encouraging others to find a meaning in their lives. There was a time when a child with any physical disability was considered a curse to the family. As a result, the innocent child was made to suffer for mistakes he had never committed and throughout his life, he would consider himself a useless burden on the planet.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> <a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/gh.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1693\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/gh.jpg\" alt=\"gh\" width=\"960\" height=\"640\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">On 23<sup>rd</sup> February 2011, when a boy named Gulshan Kumar registered his name in the Guinness Book of World Records for the highest number of 63 manual spins on a wheelchair, every parent with a child on the wheelchair must have visualized their children breaking that record in the days to come. That day, Gulshan Kumar proved to the world that a person on a wheelchair is not disabled, he is just differently abled.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Like Gulshan Kumar, there are numerous youngsters who have found a new meaning in their life owing to the commendable initiatives of the <strong>Ability Unlimited Foundation</strong>. Conceptualized by Guruji Syed Sallauddin Pasha, AUF nurtures people with disabilities and grooms them in various forms of art like classical dancing, singing etc. The beneficiaries of the foundation have performed in all parts of India and in numerous locations abroad as well and wherever they go, standing ovations after every mesmerizing performance is bound to happen.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">AUF has been rendering therapeutic healing through music and dance to hundreds of differently abled youth since 1988 and Guruji Pasha has been bringing smiles to these faces for more than 3 decades now.</p>\n<a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/as.jpg\">\n<img class=\"size-large wp-image-1692 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/as.jpg\" alt=\"as\" width=\"648\" height=\"556\" /></a>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Recently, I had a rare opportunity of witnessing and interacting with this immensely talented bunch of people when they performed in Xavier Institute of Management Bhubaneswar during the annual fest. True to their fame, they left the whole crowd mesmerized with their energy, their skills, their talent and their ever smiling faces. Be it Sufi or Bharatnatyam or Bollywood, with every spin of their wheelchairs, the whole auditorium burst into appreciative applause. What left me awestruck was the dedication these performers have towards their dance – even the limited space of the corridors in the college guest house didn’t stop them from rehearsing for their next performance!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">No matter how difficult the path may be, if you have the zeal to tread it and a pair of strong hands behind you to catch you when you fall, no one can stop you from being a shining star – the Ability Unlimited Foundation has proven it.</p>','Ability Unlimited Foundation','','publish','open','open','','ability-unlimited-foundation','','','2014-11-21 19:47:04','2014-11-21 14:17:04','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1690',0,'post','',0),(1691,2,'2014-11-21 19:41:00','2014-11-21 14:11:00','','sa','','inherit','open','open','','sa','','','2014-11-21 19:41:00','2014-11-21 14:11:00','',1690,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/sa.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1692,2,'2014-11-21 19:41:30','2014-11-21 14:11:30','','as','','inherit','open','open','','as-2','','','2014-11-21 19:41:30','2014-11-21 14:11:30','',1690,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/as.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1693,2,'2014-11-21 19:43:33','2014-11-21 14:13:33','','gh','','inherit','open','open','','gh','','','2014-11-21 19:43:33','2014-11-21 14:13:33','',1690,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/gh.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1702,22,'2014-11-23 20:34:57','2014-11-23 15:04:57','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">On this very optimistic and dreamy note, I take you into the contours of the kind of India that Modi envisions to establish! From being touted as the victory of an extremely effective PR and marketing strategy, to being coined as ‘just an eloquent orator, not much of a doer’,   this man has definitely seen highs and lows in his political career so far!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I can just render the account of what would be a lay man’s take on the India, that Mr. Modi envisages, and thus, too technical analysis of his economic and political strategies, seems far fetched at the moment! The first time that I realized that some of his ideologies are actually phenomenal, was when I very casually switched on my TV set to witness the Independence Day speech, a ritual that I have been observing since the past decade or so. Breaking the kind of morose aura, that the previous few speeches had, this one came across as a straight from the heart, no bland ‘read from the paper’ kind of a dialogue.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Speaking from probably the most responsible platform of the nation, he spoke no rocket science and just spoke on the need for a hygienic, safe, financially able, and trade aware nation. I was stunned beyond words to watch him speak on basic issues like these, and not something extravagant like space missions, or the stock market! It had all the elements that had been a reason of resentment and sorrow to the masses. From enlightening the importance of proper sanitation facilities, especially for a female, to actually discussing in elucidations on female safety, he set the trend right for himself!</p>\n<img class=\"wp-image-1720 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/bn-cx732_ijapan_g_20140523051304.jpg\" alt=\"BN-CX732_ijapan_G_20140523051304\" width=\"290\" height=\"193\" />\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">But what needs more rapt attention is the fact that he shows equal futuristic approach, with respect to establishing India as a business hub, and him welcoming Japan to collaborate with the Indian software industry, or inviting manufacturers to MAKE IN INDIA, or wanting minimum government interference wrt businesses, in order to facilitate governance are amazing footholds of visionary ideas and notions.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">And the most enticing of all aspects, was the fact that he encouraged the youth to work for India, and be entrepreneurs who manufacture at least one thing that can be exported from India. Sounds good? Sure does! He has touched upon those veins of Indian population, which were not even considered worth importance by the earlier prime ministers. Latest instance being the teacher’s day video talk across the schools of India, where he advised students to emulate voracious reading and emulate positive aspects of the practical learning in their personas!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">First develop India, a concept that he proudly upholds, or his UN speech, where he inscribed his notions of all nation meets (All-G), taking a strong stand on Pakistan at an international podium, or endorsing proper sanitation conditions and terrorism- free lives across the globe, this man is definitely a man of extremely sagacious and good- vibe ideas, a hue which I wish encompasses the nation soon with proper edifice to these ideas.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">All in all, <a title=\"Modi\" href=\"http://www.mygov.in\" target=\"_blank\"> Modi </a> is a man of extremely progressive and benevolent ideals, and endorses the notions of nation love, to one and all. I feel proud to uphold the fact that our nation finally has a prime minister who has ideals, which if applied, can take the nation to definite roads of progress!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Make in India...</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">First develop India....</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Minimum government, maximum governance!</p>','Narendra Modi ’s Chanakyaniti','','publish','open','open','','narendra-modi-s-chanakyaniti','','','2014-11-23 20:34:57','2014-11-23 15:04:57','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1702',0,'post','',2),(1704,15,'2014-11-23 16:27:15','2014-11-23 10:57:15','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">“A THING OF BEAUTY IS A JOY FOREVER”\n- JOHN  KEATS</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The dictionary meaning of environment is  particular natural surrounding in which you live or exist considered in relation to their physical characteristics or weather conditions. The environment is the natural world of land , sea , plants and animals .</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Talking of environmental devastation we are talking of all the ways and activities of us that harm the environment adversely. Destroying the environmental balance due to global warming caused by greenhouse effect is a way that harms the land. Dumping garbage or industrial effluents directly in water or throwing away the ashes of dead bodies can harm the water sources on earth . Deforestation not only causes soil erosion which adversely affects the plant life but also results in loss of shelter and homes for many birds and animals. Throwing away the garbage of our homes and littering here and there can also affect the environment in an adversarial manner. Hunting and poaching of animals had made many delicate species  go extinct and endangered.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">“What is this life , if full of care\nWe have no time to stand and stare “\n-  W.H. Davies</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The basic cause of this environmental degradation is the ruthless and selfish behavior of us towards our surroundings . And when we are confronted we give the biggest reason as DEVELOPMENT . We harm the plants and animals without even thinking that they are the reason of our maintaining the ecological balance and the life cycle .  We harm the water bodies without even thinking that they are the ones that maintain the water table. We harm the animals without thinking that without them the food web and food chain would not be possible . But in reality if we see we are not harming them but harming our very existence on  this planet . We are not progressing towards development but degrading towards severe devastation .</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">“Tiny drops of water make a mighty ocean.”\n- Julia A . F. Carney</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The solutions to these problems are many but the question of the hour is that  are we really ready for self introspection to look for the answers.  Going in depth firstly we should not let allow the increase in level of industrialization which harms the ecological balance and hence  affects  our very existence here.  Afforestation should be taken ahead and carried forward with all enthusiasm and energy .  We should not dump garbage and waste directly into water bodies without proper treatment. Moreover the emissions of smoke and harmful gases can be reduced by using less of petrol and diesel run vehicles and more of cycles and environment friendly CNG vehicles as and when required.  Animals should be treated with the same love , care and affection as humans treat their own kids and family members.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/goats-191788_640.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1727 \" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/goats-191788_640.jpg\" alt=\"goats-191788_640\" width=\"559\" height=\"425\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Talking is easy but bringing it on ground level is equally difficult . But I have taken certain steps to help my mother nature foster and grow.  I always plant a sapling in my garden on each birthday of mine and as the time passes by my friends and family celebrate my bday along with my planted saplings every year. Secondly I am very much inspired by seeing the work of Mrs . Maneka Gandhi who works whole heartedly towards the noble cause of saving animals through an organization called PETA . With this inspiration the kids of my colony and me have built small shelter homes for puppies and small injured animals in the garages of our vehicles . This noble cause was gradually appreciated by all and all people of our colony started joining in.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Hence the biggest key to uphold the degrading level of environment is through SELF INTROSPECTION and then bringing it in our daily ACTION . And instead of giving this ruthless behavior of ours the name of DEVELOPMENT  we should join hands to worlk for its upliftment , because ,</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>  “YOU ARE THEREFORE I AM”</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>','Is environmental devastation the price of development ..???','','publish','open','open','','environment-vs-development','','','2014-11-23 16:27:15','2014-11-23 10:57:15','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1704',0,'post','',0),(1706,12,'2014-11-23 20:21:45','2014-11-23 14:51:45','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Social media is not about the exploitation of technology, but service to community.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">-Simon Mainwaring</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In this day, our social surroundings pertaining to community interaction has acquired a virtual form through increasing usage of electronic gadgets. Past is the era where parks and play grounds played an important role in establishing bonds of friendship and strengthening social interaction. Now social media is the platform where people meet, exchange ideas, develop a sense of collective feeling and serve the community.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The most suitable method of spreading the idea of social service in this gadget and information driven world is through social media. The shift of emphasis from the print media to the virtual media has facilitated the movement of information across nations and people in the click of a mouse. It could be considered as the fastest means of reaching out to people. In this era with increasing number of crimes and human rights violation, it is imperative that the issue be tackled with urgency. Burying their lives in the social media is what most people today are engrossed in. Hence the best way to capture their attention is through the same way.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/social-media-keyboard.jpg\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-1746 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/social-media-keyboard-1024x682.jpg\" alt=\"Social Media\" width=\"648\" height=\"431\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Organisations working for human rights should make sure that they don’t loose out on their biggest audience by encouraging them to take part in their activities and by instigating the importance of social service. If this is not done, the people engrossed in their gadgets would be oblivious to their social surroundings and for a young and dynamic nation like India, children growing up without understanding it would be disastrous in the future. Social media also creates a feeling of collective belonging in the people. The Whatsapp, Facebook and Twitter groups form an important role in spreading awareness about social issues, encouraging people to participate in activities such as awareness campaigns and volunteering. Options for charitable donations have started being an increasingly common characteristic of many online payment portals. In a changing world of online stores and shopping mania, charitable donations made by adding some extra amount to the purchase amount as a whole could make a substantial contribution to the charitable organisations.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Moreover, social media has the power to influence and change the mindset of people to being more responsible citizens and act collectively as the part of a group. This feature of social media should be exploited for the greater good of those not being able to enjoy these privileges. The very reason for choosing to write on this topic was due to the prevalence of an increasing number of so called ‘post’s and ‘comments’ on social networking sites regarding the current social issues. Such discussion groups play an important role in understanding the perception of the people and hence enable the institutions working towards human welfare to take up actions which gain them greater support from the public.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Boundary-less contribution is what characterizes social service through social media. Irrespective of nationality and social stratification, social media is universal and equally accessible to all. Hence in spite of differences, social media has the capability of capturing a larger group of people and bring them together for a greater good. Social media is the solution to spreading awareness about social issues. This scope of social media should be employed to its fullest capability.</p>\n<a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images3.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-1747 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images3.jpg\" alt=\"images\" width=\"290\" height=\"174\" /></a>','Social Service through Social Media','','publish','open','open','','social-service-social-media','','','2014-11-23 20:21:45','2014-11-23 14:51:45','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1706',0,'post','',0),(1708,19,'2014-11-23 20:31:32','2014-11-23 20:31:32','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There is not even a single city or country where the female gender live free from the fear of violence. No super leader can claim: *NO!! NO!! This is not happening in my land or backyard*.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em><strong>Whether walking down the streets, using public transports, going to work or school, oh ya! Well kindergarten too (as the eyes of the so called GREAT PEOPLE not just restricted to 16+ or 18+) are subject to the threat of harassment. One of the major issue and burning topic of almost every country (I would rather say ALL) is ‘WOMEN SAFETY’, but still, violence and harassment against the women and girls in public spaces remains a largely neglected issue, with few laws or policies in place to address it.</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em><strong>Now the question comes, ARE STRINGENT LAWS ENOUGH TO CURB THE SEXUAL OVERDRIVE? One of the main reasons of violence against women is the mentality which deems women inferior of men and merely limits their importance to the maintenance of the household, the upbringing of children and pleasing their husbands and serving other members of the family.<a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/bigstock-friends-shopping-4317497.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1750 \" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/bigstock-friends-shopping-4317497-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"bigstock-friends-shopping-4317497\" width=\"461\" height=\"307\" /></a></strong></em>Times have changed but the mentality still prevails in the mindsets of several narrow minded people. The recent incident in which a 23-year-old paramedical student was gang-raped by 6 men inside a moving bus in Delhi shocked the nation to its core. This was reflected in the massive protests that followed the incident, demanding justice for the victim. Although it was a most heinous case of cruelty, it is ironical to note that such incidents are not actually rare in our country. There are several such cases happening everyday where females (from infants to old ladies, from upper middle class women in metro cities to dalit women in villages) are subjected to dreadful sexual torture by such nasty men.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Strong and stringent laws are definitely necessary in ensuring swift justice and appropriate punishment to the guilty. But the actual need of the hour is a revolutionary change in the mindsets and conscience of men so that they stop seeing women as objects of sexual pleasure. Each city is unique and requires a local response. It’s YOU who can bring a change, it’s WE who can do something about it. Small steps can lead to a major impact. Bring a change, at least a small change and make the world better for women and girls.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Reference- Power to change (http://powertochange.com/)</p>','Making cities safe for female gender','','publish','open','open','','making-cities-safe-female-gender','','','2014-11-23 20:31:32','2014-11-23 20:31:32','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1708',0,'post','',3),(1717,2,'2014-11-23 15:56:45','2014-11-23 10:26:45','','PM_Modi independence day_Speech_PTI','','inherit','open','open','','pm_modi-independence-day_speech_pti','','','2014-11-23 15:56:45','2014-11-23 10:26:45','',1702,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/pm_modi-independence-day_speech_pti.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1719,2,'2014-11-23 16:00:43','2014-11-23 10:30:43','','ObamaModi','','inherit','open','open','','obamamodi','','','2014-11-23 16:00:43','2014-11-23 10:30:43','',1702,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/obamamodi.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1720,2,'2014-11-23 16:00:48','2014-11-23 10:30:48','','BN-CX732_ijapan_G_20140523051304','','inherit','open','open','','bn-cx732_ijapan_g_20140523051304','','','2014-11-23 16:00:48','2014-11-23 10:30:48','',1702,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/bn-cx732_ijapan_g_20140523051304.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1727,2,'2014-11-23 16:21:53','2014-11-23 10:51:53','','goats-191788_640','','inherit','open','open','','goats-191788_640','','','2014-11-23 16:21:53','2014-11-23 10:51:53','',1704,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/goats-191788_640.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1746,2,'2014-11-23 20:18:20','2014-11-23 14:48:20','Social Media button on a keyboard with speech bubbles.','Social Media','','inherit','open','open','','social-media','','','2014-11-23 20:18:20','2014-11-23 14:48:20','',1706,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/social-media-keyboard.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1747,2,'2014-11-23 20:18:31','2014-11-23 14:48:31','','images','','inherit','open','open','','images-16','','','2014-11-23 20:18:31','2014-11-23 14:48:31','',1706,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1748,2,'2014-11-23 20:18:39','2014-11-23 14:48:39','','social media and the social worker main banner','','inherit','open','open','','social-media-and-the-social-worker-main-banner','','','2014-11-23 20:18:39','2014-11-23 14:48:39','',1706,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/social-media-and-the-social-worker-main-banner.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1750,2,'2014-11-23 20:27:49','2014-11-23 14:57:49','','bigstock-friends-shopping-4317497','','inherit','open','open','','bigstock-friends-shopping-4317497','','','2014-11-23 20:27:49','2014-11-23 14:57:49','',1708,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/bigstock-friends-shopping-4317497.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1751,2,'2014-11-23 20:28:08','2014-11-23 14:58:08','','rtx12u6v','','inherit','open','open','','rtx12u6v','','','2014-11-23 20:28:08','2014-11-23 14:58:08','',1708,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/rtx12u6v.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1752,2,'2014-11-23 20:28:31','2014-11-23 14:58:31','','toi-eight-ways-to-make-nation_s-rape-capital-safer-for-women1','','inherit','open','open','','toi-eight-ways-to-make-nation_s-rape-capital-safer-for-women1','','','2014-11-23 20:28:31','2014-11-23 14:58:31','',1708,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/toi-eight-ways-to-make-nation_s-rape-capital-safer-for-women1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1755,12,'2014-11-23 21:16:30','2014-11-23 15:46:30','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The long queues in front of the beverage corporation outlets describe best the enchantment that alcohol has created in Kerala. Having an average annual alcohol consumption of 8.3 litres against a national average of 5 litres, Kerala still retains its position as the front-runner in the consumption of alcohol in India. In a state where alcohol plays conflicting roles of bringing in 22% of the total revenue, 8000 crore out of excise tax on one hand and reasons for 40% of road accidents and 60% of divorce cases, the prohibition of alcohol requires to be judged upon the impact it will have on the economy and the society. The decision pertaining to the greater good should be adopted rather than a hasty one.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The policy of complete prohibition which in fact was taken as a part of a political melodrama, has now acquired a permanent position in all discussion circles in Kerala. Organisations such as Women’s Groups, Human Rights Organisations and other Welfare organisations have extended their support to the policy and they strongly vouch for the proper implementation of it. Considering the issue from the current scenario of increasing alcohol sales and corresponding increase in societal discord, it could be assumed that prohibition is the key to all these problems. But it should be understood that complete prohibition, even though gradual, might result in greater familial disruptions and societal disintegration because in a state where the number of drinkers are tremendously high, it might not be possible for them to adjust to the change as expected. Hence the implementation of a policy whose result is not definite should be undertaken with proper monitoring.</p>\n<a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/img_1481.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-1756 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/img_1481-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"img_1481\" width=\"321\" height=\"241\" /></a>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Also, India’s history of failed alcohol prohibition acts such as that in Tamil Nadu and Haryana should also be taken into account while considering the plausibility of the new alcohol policy in Kerala. The prohibition policy in Haryana led to a simultaneous hike in transport, electricity and power charges. What led to the failure of the policy was the difficulty in acceptance of these policies by the public.  Hence, there should not only be scope for changes in other policies, but in the mindset of people as well. They should be eager to adapt to the drastic change in social surrounding that would entail the policy implementation. Failure in this context will inevitably lead to the failure in the policy itself coupled with the huge loss in the state exchequer.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Another important aspect that would follow the policy would be the widened inequality among the rich and the poor. The current High Court judgement regarding the closure of all the bars other than five-star ones evidently highlights the bias faced by those who cannot afford them. This conundrum will implicitly affect the youth since them being more instinctive, would eventually look for alternate methods of alcohol procurement which could lead to the emergence of an illegal market and increased smuggling from neighbour states.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The plausibility of successful implementation of the prohibition policy in Kerala could be challenged on the basis of various factors. An important question to be answered is that why one segment of the society should be denied of their right while the other enjoys it?</p>\n&nbsp;','Kerala and its alcohol game','','publish','open','open','','kerala-alcohol-game','','','2014-11-23 21:16:30','2014-11-23 15:46:30','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1755',0,'post','',1),(1756,2,'2014-11-23 21:11:46','2014-11-23 15:41:46','','img_1481','','inherit','open','open','','img_1481','','','2014-11-23 21:11:46','2014-11-23 15:41:46','',1755,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/img_1481.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1757,2,'2014-11-23 21:12:04','2014-11-23 15:42:04','','207_drinks','','inherit','open','open','','207_drinks','','','2014-11-23 21:12:04','2014-11-23 15:42:04','',1755,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/207_drinks.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1758,2,'2014-11-23 21:12:16','2014-11-23 15:42:16','','kerala-alchohol-prohibition','','inherit','open','open','','kerala-alchohol-prohibition','','','2014-11-23 21:12:16','2014-11-23 15:42:16','',1755,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/kerala-alchohol-prohibition.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1766,19,'2014-11-24 13:18:11','2014-11-24 07:48:11','','2278669523_9e1239eee0_z','','inherit','open','open','','2278669523_9e1239eee0_z','','','2014-11-24 13:18:11','2014-11-24 07:48:11','',0,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2278669523_9e1239eee0_z.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1771,19,'2014-11-24 18:51:10','2014-11-24 13:21:10','','1460223_656150271096240_183271057_n','','inherit','open','open','','1460223_656150271096240_183271057_n','','','2014-11-24 18:51:10','2014-11-24 13:21:10','',1708,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/1460223_656150271096240_183271057_n.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1807,21,'2014-11-26 10:13:27','2014-11-26 10:13:27','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As dusk gave way to darkness  amid slight drizzle and a pleasant breeze , I patiently stood at the side of the road , waiting for a bus that would take me home. Standing there , under the orange hue of a nearby street lamp , drenched slightly from the rain and tired after the day\'s errands, I had no inklings of the adventures that evening held for me. A loud honk, doused  the usual noise and din created by vendors , small cars and bikes , causing a marked change in activity around me. Everyone started to excitedly run towards an approaching bus sounding the alarm, and knowing that \"order\" is something no one here knew of , I began running too. The bus was already overloaded , yet people continued to board it amid encouraging remarks from those behind to keep moving. Pushed and pulled, I somehow managed to make it to aisle , but the sea of humans obstructed any further movement. The dimly lit interiors exuded a mixed smell of sweat and bedis. As of habit I felt my pockets cautious against pickpockets that frequent crowded buses . To my despair, the worst of my fears came true as my wallet went missing. I knew that the notorious Indian pickpocket had outsmarted me and this incident would go down in that endless list of legends that every parent warns his child against. I looked around hoping to find the man to did this but to no avail. I was helpless , the only money left on me was a ten rupee note which would not even suffice for the fare of the journey. I instantly raised an alarm but nobody knew of my missing wallet. I gave the conductor the ten rupee note I had and the good man , aware of my misfortune ,did not ask for more. I felt grim. My driving license and ATM card were gone too with the wallet. I was full of perspiration sandwiched between human bodies , helpless and penniless .</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Soon those around started offering opinions. One said : \" You may have dropped it\".Another : \" Tell the thief to take your money and leave the license\". But all unanimously agreed that God does not favour people of such malicious intent.  A few asked if I had enough on me to get me home. I would manage , I replied.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">After some time the bus stopped and a few people got off. I saw my chance to look under the seats. Nothing. But then I saw a police officer in the front seat, thought he might help . So I went up to him. He looked at me sheepishly .</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\" What\'s wrong son? \" , he asked.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\"I lost a black wallet\", that sheepish look did not leave his face.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Puzzled he asked: \"What is a wallet? \" . I knew I would never find it.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I was left to wonder about the hand of the Indian pickpocket that has relentlessly searched almost every Indian pocket and rendered it empty of any object it may have contained. That hand which must slip into a new pocket each time to quench its master\'s avirice. A hand that has learnt to rob another farmers harvest and is unwilling to toil honestly. Such a hand has no place in my country.</p>','The Lost Wallet','','publish','open','open','','lost-wallet','','','2014-11-26 10:13:27','2014-11-26 10:13:27','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1807',0,'post','',7),(1809,2,'2014-11-26 10:08:33','2014-11-26 04:38:33','Lost wallet','Lost wallet','','inherit','open','open','','maxresdefault','','','2014-11-26 10:08:33','2014-11-26 04:38:33','',1807,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/maxresdefault.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1810,2,'2014-11-26 10:09:54','2014-11-26 04:39:54','','mumbai-pickpocket-demo-1','','inherit','open','open','','mumbai-pickpocket-demo-1','','','2014-11-26 10:09:54','2014-11-26 04:39:54','',1807,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/mumbai-pickpocket-demo-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1815,17,'2014-11-26 23:06:39','2014-11-26 17:36:39','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Even in the 21<sup>st</sup> century when India has reached to the ‘red’ Mars and back, majority of the Indians are still obsessed with ‘brown’, ‘black’ and ‘white’. I am talking about the different categories into which our complexions are divided into. To the rest of the world, India is still a land of browns and to the Indians, India is a land of fairness creams.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This article of mine doesn’t mean to undermine or cut through the market share of fairness creams in India (I wouldn’t dare! It is one of the largest contributors to the Indian FMCG market). What this article aims is to point out the thought process of Indians and their biasness towards the color white.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In the outside world when such biasness is referred to as racism, in India, it is just an outlook and a personal preference. What everyone overlooks is the fact that the preference of someone might be the reason of depression for someone else. Even worse is the plight of the girls – no matter how educated you are, no matter how intelligent you are, no matter how good you cook, no matter how perfectly you sing or dance, at the end of the day, you would definitely come across someone who would undermine your achievements with your complexion.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">While writing this article, the thought that is running at the back of my mind is the matrimonial ads displayed in the newspapers where a fair bride is the need of the hour – just like the fact that the metric of a potential groom is his salary package. Just because a girl has more reactive melanin pigment, she is destined to be doomed for the rest of her life.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Now one can argue that the attitudes of the people are changing and today’s youth prefer brains over looks. But the frequency at which fairness creams are sold in India tell me a completely different story. And the most fearful part is that the girls themselves have developed an abysmal self-esteem and are tremendously conscious of their skin color. They think very low about their skin color and consider that the whole world will come to an end if their complexions do not resemble that of milk smeared with saffron.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I have personally talked with quite a number of girls asking about the reason as to why they are so doubtful about their complexion. These girls are smart, intelligent and successful in their jobs but still are extremely under-confident. The reason that majority of them give is that they have been made conscious about their dark skin right from their childhood, if not by their parents, by their relatives and over the years, this thought gets so much deep rooted in their minds that they end up feeling unsure about themselves and this gets reflected in their work.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/a.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1816\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/a.jpg\" alt=\"fair skin\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">My concern is if our ‘well-wishers’ don’t wish our wellness anymore, then who will? It is high time, this mentality is changed and the change has to be initiated by us – the youth of India. Gone are the days when a bride is deemed fit for marriage or not by the precision she pours tea in the cup or the way she walks or how tasty she cooks biryani. In a timeline when girls have come to the forefront taking up responsibilities in every walk of professional and personal life, an issue as trivial as skin color should be pushed to the farthest of oblivion.</p>','In Search of Fair Skin','','publish','open','open','','search-fair-skin','','','2014-11-26 23:06:39','2014-11-26 17:36:39','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1815',0,'post','',2),(1816,2,'2014-11-26 23:00:42','2014-11-26 17:30:42','Fair Skin','a','','inherit','open','open','','a','','','2014-11-26 23:00:42','2014-11-26 17:30:42','',1815,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/a.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1817,2,'2014-11-26 23:01:12','2014-11-26 17:31:12','','s','','inherit','open','open','','s','','','2014-11-26 23:01:12','2014-11-26 17:31:12','',1815,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/s.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1819,20,'2014-11-27 00:15:32','2014-11-26 18:45:32','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Recently, we have seen a shocking incident about how a girl was allegedly murdered because she married a youth belonging to a different caste. Her own parents committed this heinous crime. SHOCKING!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As defined in a dictionary, love is a deep, tender, ineffable feeling of affection and solicitude towards a person, recognition of attractive qualities, or a sense of underlying oneness. Why is it so difficult for people to understand it?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We have always heard that parents have selfless love for their children. They sacrifice their happiness for their children to be happy. But this incident indicates something else.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Those who believe in God, they would also believe that humans are creations of God, right? The rest might think that this concept is not realistic, well; we also know that the humans are evolved from the monkeys, correct? We all have been monkeys and <em>aadi vaasis </em>in the past. Why differentiate now? Why does the caste matter now?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/33a39da16f9c2c73a9e1ecf378db887a_l.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-1820\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/33a39da16f9c2c73a9e1ecf378db887a_l.jpg\" alt=\"Love\" width=\"330\" height=\"244\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I know so many happy couples, Hindu-Muslim, Hindu-Christian and even couples who had inter-caste marriages. They are happy because they are accepted, if not by the society, they were accepted by their parents, their loved ones. Nothing else matters more than that.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">But, some people never change I guess. It’s like yelling at the wall to move. If I could ask for one wish, I would ask for people to understand LOVE. Alas! The language of violence is understood more than love. For me, love will always be a bliss and never a sin!</p>','Love- A Bliss or Sin ?','','publish','open','open','','love-bliss-sin','','','2014-11-27 00:15:32','2014-11-26 18:45:32','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1819',0,'post','',2),(1820,2,'2014-11-26 23:48:08','2014-11-26 18:18:08','','33a39da16f9c2c73a9e1ecf378db887a_L','','inherit','open','open','','33a39da16f9c2c73a9e1ecf378db887a_l','','','2014-11-26 23:48:08','2014-11-26 18:18:08','',1819,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/33a39da16f9c2c73a9e1ecf378db887a_l.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1823,2,'2014-11-27 00:22:38','2014-11-26 18:52:38','The Hands Of An Indian Gujarati Bride And Bridegroom, A Ritual Performed In An Indian Gujarati Wedding, India','3','','inherit','open','open','','3-2','','','2014-11-27 00:22:38','2014-11-26 18:52:38','',1819,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1824,23,'2014-12-06 00:52:39','2014-12-05 19:22:39','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The society has a habit of defining everything. Especially what is normal and what is not normal. So, when my sister was born with an extra chromosome, they told us she wasn\'t normal. Their reasons being she would be a slow - learner, would find it hard to tie her shoe laces and it would be extremely difficult for her to go through life. Moreover, they easily tagged her as a burden we had to carry with us all our lives. They had defined her on the number of chromosomes she had-she wasn\'t normal.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">She has a condition called Down\'s Syndrome. She is sixteen now. She does find it hard to tie her shoe laces, so we buy her shoes with velcro. She is a little slow with academics and has taught us patience. However, she has proved the society to be wrong. She is living her life, dancing to every song she hears. She is hardly a burden on her family. She is more like an asset. Every day after I reach home, she heats up my food in the microwave and gives me my lunch. It is true that she can\'t talk and has never told me that she loves me but whenever she goes out to the market, she makes sure she gets something for me. Souvenirs of her love, no?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Sixteen years ago, the society told us that tragedy had struck us because of the little baby born with Down\'s Syndrome. She changed our lives, but in all sorts of good ways. She may be tiny and possess weak vocal chords but she made us change our definition of \'normal\'. Toni Morrison says that definitions are for the definer, not for the defined. Hence, I believe it is very important for us as a society to look at how inhumane we act when we tag someone as a liability just because they\'re not like the rest of us. We refuse to embrace their differences. I am not saying these \'disabled\' individuals need help. I\'m saying they need to be embraced. They are a little different but it doesn\'t take away from the fact that they\'re human beings too. A person is just as disabled as you treat him to be.</p>','How Normal ?','','publish','open','open','','normal','','','2014-12-06 00:52:39','2014-12-05 19:22:39','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1824',0,'post','',5),(1831,12,'2014-11-27 14:31:33','2014-11-27 09:01:33','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">That smell of soil when the first drop of rain touches the earth, the winding roads through forests, the chirping birds, sound of animals and ultimately that breath of fresh air is what everybody longs for when they need a break. In the words of Franklin D Roosevelt, “Forests are the lungs of our land, purifying the air and giving fresh strength to the people”. Forests are not merely a patch of greenery. It has life and it sustains life. Erasing the forest would imply erasing mankind.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">India has been blessed with a great forest cover which was sufficient enough to sustain mankind for eternity. But have we been able to retain this blessing? Definitely not. The mighty Western Ghats is spread over six states in the Southern and Western India and is home to a diverse ecosystem. It covers an area of nearly 1,65,000 square kilometres. A train or a flight journey through the Konkan route will show you the powerful Western Ghats with all its glory. But to realise that only 41% of the forest cover is what remains in this region with 59% already prone to exploitation is a thought to be pondered about and taken action against.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">On the other hand lays the biggest prospective revenue earning industry in India: Mining. Western Ghats has been ruthlessly exploited for Mining and Quarrying. This industry could elevate the growth of Indian economy to 10-12% growth, create 13 million employment opportunities and increase the royalty collection by 5 times. The question is whether India is ready to forgo its fresh air for its position as a developed nation. If yes, how long will this position last if this development means nothing to the people affected by it? Is it worth the number of lives lost, the tress cut and the flora and fauna wiped out of the country?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Kasturirangan Report recommended that 37% of area in the Western Ghats be considered as Ecologically Sensitive Area (ESA) and all forms of industrial activities banned. But states of Karnataka and Kerala have protested against this recommendation saying that it will lead to a setback in their developmental process. But how sustainable will this development mean? Stripping such pristine regions off its resources and expanding industrial and agricultural sectors would entail shortage of resources in the future and would result in disastrous natural calamities.<a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/download1.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1833\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/download1.jpg\" alt=\"Mining in ghats\" width=\"275\" height=\"183\" /></a> Why is there a need to keep the lives of people at stake in the name of development and growth? The major mining companies like TISCO, Vedanta, S R Rungta etc are undoubtedly contributing a large amount to the national product. But the result of such exploitation can be seen in various parts of country like Jharkhand and Orissa where increased amount of Arsenic, Manganese, Uranium and other radioactive pollutants are found in the river. Coupled with this is the hydro and nuclear power projects which will have adverse effects on land, soil and livelihood for generations to come. Loss of biodiversity, obstruction in the ecological flow of rivers, destruction of habitation of animals and plants, loss of livelihood for the local people are the direct impact of such exploitation. Lack of efficient implementation of rehabilitation policies and lack of sustainable strategies for the efficient utilisation of resources would lead to further devastation of communities and nature. Western Ghats should be protected from this kind of exploitation to ensure that at least the last remaining strip of land is preserved. So let us all fight for our mighty Western Ghats. I definitely want to see a Indian map with more green in it.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>','Save the mighty Ghats','','publish','open','open','','save-mighty-ghats','','','2014-11-27 14:31:33','2014-11-27 09:01:33','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1831',0,'post','',0),(1832,2,'2014-11-27 14:28:39','2014-11-27 08:58:39','','ghats','','inherit','open','open','','12570356826ed8cee9b4blq3','','','2014-11-27 14:28:39','2014-11-27 08:58:39','',1831,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/12570356826ed8cee9b4blq3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1833,2,'2014-11-27 14:30:43','2014-11-27 09:00:43','','download','','inherit','open','open','','download-3','','','2014-11-27 14:30:43','2014-11-27 09:00:43','',1831,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/download1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1837,18,'2014-12-11 15:37:45','2014-12-11 15:37:45','<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Two facing honk merely cried for their own maestro voice. Two minutes to adjust the so-called level of humanism effect. Ordered here to not loud, just to save them for another fest. The honk of my part is not very far to be hated, the other side honk is not merely causing for the cacophony of my snooze. But the colors here not permit to enter in other’s premises. The faces of same texture have a little alter in their honk. The two must have to awake by their own arrow by their own honk. Must have the same texture around the cacophonic harmony of their metals, their arms, their power, their fake honk. Pandemonium of my jingles creates more clear the level of that gospel truth of that honk. Somewhere between those loud honk saw a daisy in graveyard, a star trying to finds the perfect integrity with their specific honk and colors of devotion.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Lost serendipity looking for the justification of that honks mystification. It’s hard to understand why these honks are not composing harmony of life. These two different colored honks can harmonize the awaking of all living more pleasant then ever. Instead of sparking the light they are emitting the dark side of the maestro voice. The two honks connecting each other’s sides now the cause of the segregation of human’s immortality. Even a nebulous wave’s can feel the fresh eternal discord from the carcass of fleshy booms. The two most prominent color which Indian National have their own perspective. Even our National Revolutionaries need to solve that puzzle by adjusting the white band between those beautiful colors of fortune. The two facing each other for such a long era now comes up with their specific honks in their hand. The two brothers with their white kurta now standing with their green and saffron band, which indicates their courage and fertility, their strength and their growth. Nobody can understand the feeling of segregation from the right to be honk. Loud sound of their cherish faces can detect the virus of being human but the tight band of different perception with same devotion will never allow to be the same. That’s why we need a white band between those two powerful, prosperous but the same clan of nation’s brotherhood. We just can’t wait for the same frequency or harmony from the much known honk of our Indian Integrity. Our honks need to be adjust by our young engineers, we can tight those loosen nut and bolts by having the same color band on our serendipity.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/loud.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1969\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/loud-300x167.jpg\" alt=\"loud\" width=\"408\" height=\"227\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">(This article is dedicated to the citizen of Loudspeaker Riot Nation….)</p>','The Two Honks','','publish','open','open','','two-honks','','','2014-12-11 15:37:45','2014-12-11 15:37:45','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1837',0,'post','',1),(1841,2,'2014-11-27 23:58:49','2014-11-27 18:28:49','','b2','','inherit','open','open','','b2-3','','','2014-11-27 23:58:49','2014-11-27 18:28:49','',0,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/b22.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1842,2,'2014-11-28 00:22:22','2014-11-27 18:52:22','','header','','inherit','open','open','','header','','','2014-11-28 00:22:22','2014-11-27 18:52:22','',0,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/header.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1846,23,'2014-12-01 17:47:29','2014-12-01 12:17:29','Dear boys\n\nWe, girls, understand that you watch various films where the hero stares at the girl, follows her and suddenly they fall in love. However, we want to burst your bubble. The real world does not work this way. No girl wants to be stared at and stalking a girl would only creep her out. Please ask your mother or sister about it. We\'re sure they would share the same sort of feeling. We understand that there are certain Bollywood style tried and tested methods, but procuring a girl\'s number and playing the \'guess who\' game with her is transgressing her personal boundary. Girls have certain notions about love. Every girl harbours a dream about bumping into the love of her life at any café while reading a book. Yes, we are influenced by the media too. But, we\'re creatures of love. Staring like you\'re trying to burn holes through us does not come across as love. Following us around comes across as a very creepy move and activates our red alert phase. We want you to court us but not against our wishes. Please stop trying to act like the hero from the movie released last week.\n\n<a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/eve-copy.jpg\">\n</a> <a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/eve_teasing_1_by_ayshafaseeh-d5olvqm.jpg\">\n</a> <a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/eve-1-copy.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1849\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/eve-1-copy-1024x723.jpg\" alt=\"eve 1 copy\" width=\"648\" height=\"457\" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\nAlso, just so we\'re clear, we own our own bodies. Every bit of it. We can wear shorts. We can wear skirts. This means we\'re giving in to the fashion world. However,  this does not mean that we are \'advanced\'. No, boys, it is not an invitation. You want to steal a touch from the girl sitting next to you in the metro? Please don\'t.  We\'ve changed considerably since the past few centuries and will not hesitate to use our pepper spray or serve you with a court notice.\n\nYou set limits on us. Regarding time, clothes and all sorts of other everyday things. Just so you know,  we demand that you please set limits on yourself too. Limits like not whistling at every girl walking past you or not taking pictures without the girl\'s permission.\n\nWe can only hope you understand. Masculinity does not lie in taking control and having your way, boys. A real man makes sure he doesn\'t make a woman uncomfortable and respects every woman around him. Please take care of all the things mentioned.\n\n<a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/eve_teasing_1_by_ayshafaseeh-d5olvqm.jpg\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-1848 aligncenter\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/eve_teasing_1_by_ayshafaseeh-d5olvqm-710x1024.jpg\" alt=\"eve_teasing_1_by_ayshafaseeh-d5olvqm\" width=\"648\" height=\"934\" /></a>\n\nYours sincerely,\n\nAll the girls','Letter from a girl to all the Rowdy Rathores','','publish','open','open','','letter-girl-rowdy-rathores','','','2014-12-01 17:47:29','2014-12-01 12:17:29','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1846',0,'post','',4),(1847,2,'2014-12-01 17:42:22','2014-12-01 12:12:22','','eve copy','','inherit','open','open','','eve-copy','','','2014-12-01 17:42:22','2014-12-01 12:12:22','',1846,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/eve-copy.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1848,2,'2014-12-01 17:43:45','2014-12-01 12:13:45','','eve_teasing_1_by_ayshafaseeh-d5olvqm','','inherit','open','open','','eve_teasing_1_by_ayshafaseeh-d5olvqm','','','2014-12-01 17:43:45','2014-12-01 12:13:45','',1846,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/eve_teasing_1_by_ayshafaseeh-d5olvqm.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1849,2,'2014-12-01 17:43:56','2014-12-01 12:13:56','','eve 1 copy','','inherit','open','open','','eve-1-copy','','','2014-12-01 17:43:56','2014-12-01 12:13:56','',1846,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/eve-1-copy.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1852,2,'2014-12-06 00:49:46','2014-12-05 19:19:46','','normal_people_scare_me_by_g0rillazevr123-d4l2t43','','inherit','open','open','','normal_people_scare_me_by_g0rillazevr123-d4l2t43','','','2014-12-06 00:49:46','2014-12-05 19:19:46','',1824,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/normal_people_scare_me_by_g0rillazevr123-d4l2t43.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1854,17,'2014-12-06 10:49:56','2014-12-06 05:19:56','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">How many of us reading this article has experienced how it feels when one doesn’t get food during the times of hunger? I am not talking about those exam nights when all of a sudden you felt hungry in the hostel and your roommate had eaten up your biscuits the night before. I am talking about the situation that millions of Indians face every day – when the father returns home to the starved faces of his children, when the mother gives away her share of the meager meal because her child looked at her plate with hungry eyes, the elder brother who stole from the grocery store, got caught and beaten up only to reveal that he has a hungry sister waiting at home. I am talking about food wastage and how millions of Indians sleep hungry every night when we don’t think twice before leaving the dinner plate full of wasted food.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">According to the latest report by the United Nations Development Program, there is around 40% of food wastage in India. Converted to money terms, it amounts to around INR 58000. Bhook is an organization which works towards eradication of hunger in India. According to a survey conducted by this organization, about 20 crore Indians sleep without having dinner and around 7 million children died last year from malnutrition.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/sdsd.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1858\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/sdsd.jpg\" alt=\"sdsd\" width=\"513\" height=\"385\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A lot of NGOs are working towards this mission of eradicating hunger from India. And for that various programs like administering balanced food to the children, health checkup camps etc. are organized. However, there are a lot which the upper strata of the society where we belong to, can do.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Let’s begin with taking as much on the plate as we can eat. When we have the option of second helping, I don’t see a point of stuffing our plate with all the food items and then ending up eating nothing! The sense of avoidance of food wastage has to be inculcated in the minds of the children right at the time they start eating on their own. This is because that is the time when they tend to waste food the most.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Most of the corporate offices have various policies to prevent food wastage among its employees. Although there has been a substantial decrease in the amount of food wastage, the figure hasn’t come down impressively. That means, there is an essential need to increase the sense of saving food amidst the youth. There is a need to set examples and ask the others to follow the noble lead.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Care has to be taken to prevent the wastage of uncooked food as well. According to a news report by BBC, India wastes about 7 billion worth of raw food materials every year. This is because of the scarcity of cold storages. Since there is no way in which the produced food materials can be stored for a longer period of time, they rot on their way from the villages to the markets in the cities.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">According to Mr. Pradipta Sen, the head of a cold storage warehousing company, the prices of fruits and vegetables can be reduced by about 30-40% if they could be stored properly before reaching the market places. These figures are proof enough to show that the solution lies right in front of us while we still crib about poverty and hunger.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/sds.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-1859\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/sds.jpg\" alt=\"Hungry children\" width=\"295\" height=\"202\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The path is long and the destination is far off. However, it is necessary that we take the baby steps and embark upon this mission of preventing food wastage, thereby helping in the noble endeavor to set a plate of food in front of those million hungry children.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>','How it feels to sleep Hungry most of the nights?','','publish','open','open','','feels-sleep-hungry-nights','','','2014-12-06 10:49:56','2014-12-06 05:19:56','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1854',0,'post','',3),(1856,2,'2014-12-06 10:46:12','2014-12-06 05:16:12','','sss','','inherit','open','open','','sss','','','2014-12-06 10:46:12','2014-12-06 05:16:12','',1854,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/sss.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1858,2,'2014-12-06 10:46:59','2014-12-06 05:16:59','','sdsd','','inherit','open','open','','sdsd','','','2014-12-06 10:46:59','2014-12-06 05:16:59','',1854,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/sdsd.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1859,2,'2014-12-06 10:47:52','2014-12-06 05:17:52','','sds','','inherit','open','open','','sds','','','2014-12-06 10:47:52','2014-12-06 05:17:52','',1854,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/sds.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1861,18,'2014-12-06 11:16:49','2014-12-06 05:46:49','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">How far is Mars from Earth? How far is Pokemon from my television? We human can calculate the distance perfectly, but how far my doll is from me? Is that a tough question to my urban folks, not exactly? Than why i afraid to demand this from my own society, just because that i am a boy not a girl. I am neither in black nor in white, even not in the third gender. I am simply and naturally a boy. A boy with masculine trait, but i like dolls, Barbie, bangles, nail paint. This society has done something extraordinary for genders. A Boy can never cry, if he ever tried than surely someone from this civilized society crowned up him with the title of girl and humiliated by the taunt, <em>‘Aurton jaise ro rahe ho’</em>. A girl can never fight and if she does, again someone from this civilized society come up with a very famous quote “<em>khub ladi mardani wo to Jhansi wali Rani thi”</em>  we all have heard about the brave Laxmibai, Rani of Jhansi, she fought for the nation, she fought for her people. But over intellectual human we are, again crowned up this brave idol of India as “<em>mardani”</em>. Bravery is still seen as a masculine virtue, no matter how many women or how few men display it. We have different parameters for both men and women, we cannot cross the socially constructed definition of gender. If a girl’s attire is formal Shirt and Trouser than it appears good because it reflects the adaptation of man characteristic by women. And if a boy ever try to cover his entire natural biological body with socially structured women’s attire than it’s totally a matter of shame for him.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This starts from our childhood when boys and girls are trained in appropriate, gender-specific forms of behavior, play, dress and so on. My gender is not biological, it is just a socially constructed norm. Than why I should play with ball and bat. Is that patriarchy or by misfortune that male section have always faced the competition to be on top for everything and for that we trained for years. We really don’t care about the sensitive human side, and in return we do the same thing. We are made to follow those norms, those rituals that can not be change without breaking the deadlock of orthodox ideology. Here my own imagination is bound between those unbreakable strings. After so much assumption, theory, statement i failed to achievement my fantasy through my society. This society will not going to give us anything , if we really want our individual freedom than we need another revolution against the way society allow us survive. In current scenario, freedom changes country to country and even within parts of the country. Women enjoy less freedom than men, individual freedom of choice for both men and women is under review. And we are looking forward to attain a restriction free society by having actual freedom of choice. We do not need amendment in our constitution, we just need transformation in the perception of our society towards Gender sensitization. And right to choose the perfect life that we want. Let see How far we need to GO.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p><a href=\"http://online.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052748703922804576300903183512350\" title=\"Wsj\">Images Courtesy</a>','How far my world is ??','','publish','open','open','','far-world','','','2014-12-06 11:16:49','2014-12-06 05:46:49','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1861',0,'post','',7),(1862,2,'2014-12-06 11:10:27','2014-12-06 05:40:27','','OB-NT608_Crying_G_20110503222502','','inherit','open','open','','ob-nt608_crying_g_20110503222502','','','2014-12-06 11:10:27','2014-12-06 05:40:27','',1861,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/ob-nt608_crying_g_20110503222502-e1417844708609.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1868,21,'2014-12-06 11:52:00','2014-12-06 06:22:00','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Remember the gentleman who guarded the gates of your college or the watchman in your hostel? I am sure you remember this person who you walked past every day.  These men are generally old. The lean figure and the white beard testify. They are friendly and kind. They sometimes even help you sneak out and offer advice when you are in a fix. But have you ever wondered if the old man is meant for the job?  Yet they must perform them lest they sleep on empty stomachs.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I have often wondered how these men must feel. I notice the night watchman in my hostel. All night he sits on a chair, with a thin shawl wrapped around to shelter himself from the cold. He sits by the gate,his stick leaning on the wall and he stares out. There is no one to give him company. The cold is unforgiving but still out there alone must be cruel. I wonder what he must think. Night after night.I tried talking to him once, but the man can hardly hear. Sometimes a different guard is on duty. He too is a very old man. \"I used to be a doctor\", he once told me.  Another old guard told me he had once served in the army.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">These old men tend gardens , drive rikshaws and take up other odd jobs . You see them everywhere. They are the \"Ramu Kakas\" of bollywood. It is a very sad scenario. At an age when a man must reap the rewards of his youthful labours and must bask in the sun, these poor old men continue to work. As young men they had been assets to the country, they had served her well. Yet now there is no one to look after them. They have gained nothing. Instead, they spend their last remaining years shivering in the cold. Are we Indians too taken up by the race for being a developed country that we stop being human ?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">India is a young country. This means in time to come, we will have as many elderly  people. We really need to take a harder look at the present circumstances and makely timely amends. A report brought out jointly by United Nations Population Fund and Help Age International sais that the number of elder , will incerase by 360%.  The government should start preparing, lest we head a crisis. Let us not abandon those who nurtured us.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>','The crisis of AGED','','publish','open','open','','crisis-aged','','','2014-12-06 11:52:00','2014-12-06 06:22:00','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1868',0,'post','',4),(1870,2,'2014-12-06 11:51:14','2014-12-06 06:21:14','','Respect-for-this-Old-Man-for-His-Hard-Work-in-India','','inherit','open','open','','respect-for-this-old-man-for-his-hard-work-in-india','','','2014-12-06 11:51:14','2014-12-06 06:21:14','',1868,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/respect-for-this-old-man-for-his-hard-work-in-india.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1892,24,'2014-12-09 22:30:29','2014-12-09 17:00:29','<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Today I left from home just like any other day. The bright new morning,the birds chirps filled me with enthusiasm. The day went well except that my phone went dead. By the time I reached back home I was too eager to check up on my phone. What greeted me though as phone breathed into life was not anywhere near pleasing. Images of a church burnt down in the central city of Delhi, tensed believers outside the church, candle light rallies etc flooded my inbox. Its then I noticed that panic had already struck my household. My parents had been worrying about me getting home safe and not being able to reach my cell added to their worry.I was instantly reminded of the story by Amitav Ghosh- Ghost of Mrs.Gandhi.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">My pleadings to join the march the next day was met with a definite no.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">When I was left to myself, my thoughts went back to the history/civics lessons from school. Our books taught us that our country India is country proud of its diverseness. Great leaders like Ambedkar, Gandhi, Jhansi ki rani walked together breaking caste, race, religious and gender based barriers. The love for their country made them fight not only the British rule but also the in-house discriminations. I wondered how they would have reacted to this mishap. They would have said \"hamari saari mehnat mitti mein mil gai\".</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">No religion teaches himsa. No religion encourages communal violence. No religion teaches to look down on the lowly. All faith is based on love.Our constitution bestows the right to each Indian to follow and practice any religion. We are all bound by the same thread of nationality, then why do we discriminate? We fought and won the Britishers but why do we still succumb to religious discriminations? Why are we hurting religious sentiments? Why can not any of us practice our faith? Why do the religious minorities have to always live as preys? Why did terms like martyrs come into use? Oh! Why can not we just live in brotherly love and harmony?</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">The words of Rabindranath Tagore fills me with hope,</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Where the mind is without fear and the head is held high;Where knowledge is free;Where the world has not been broken up into fragments by narrow domestic walls;Where words come out from the depth of truth;Where tireless striving stretches its arms towards perfection;Where the clear stream of reason has not lost its way into the dreary desert sand of dead habit;Where the mind is led forward by thee into ever-widening thought and action;Into that heaven of freedom, Father, let my country awake.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">P.S: I convinced my parents into allowing me to join the peace march. After all its the youth of today that are the future of <span class=\"aBn\" tabindex=\"0\" data-term=\"goog_1748056792\"><span class=\"aQJ\">tomorrow</span></span>.</p>','A page from Diary of a youth from a religious minority','','publish','open','open','','page-diary-youth-religious-minority','','','2014-12-09 22:30:29','2014-12-09 17:00:29','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1892',0,'post','',0),(1896,2,'2014-12-09 22:27:41','2014-12-09 16:57:41','','Religious Minority Helpiez','','inherit','open','open','','g-c-woolley-page-of-diary-no2','','','2014-12-09 22:27:41','2014-12-09 16:57:41','',1892,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/g-c-woolley-page-of-diary-no2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1900,21,'2014-12-09 22:45:06','2014-12-09 17:15:06','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">According to a report by the World Health Organization, suicide is the third most prominent cause of death among the youth and on an average, a person commits suicide every 40 seconds and there are 20 failed attempts per suicide. According to the National Crime Records Bureau, Ministry of Home Affairs, the rate of suicides among the youth in India has risen to 11.4% per 1,00,000 population.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The figures may sound disturbing, but that is the reality and it is high time this issue is addressed. The ever increasing competition, constant comparison with peers, the mental stress to succeed as early in life as possible, cases of losing one’s romantic interest, everything piles up and poses an immense burden on the heads of the young people, thereby forcing them to take the extreme step.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Reports also reveal that majority of these suicides don’t occur in the spur of the moment. They are all well planned and every step is carried out in a systematic manner which bears testimony to the fact that the idea of ending something as precious as life took birth in the mind well before the task was actually executed.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Nowadays, psychiatrists are coming forward with all sorts of help needed to bring these derailed youth to the good path of life. They collaborate with hospitals, NGOs, private clinics as well as rural dispensaries. People come to them with problems, talk with them and leave as a much better person.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1905\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/suveere.jpg\" alt=\"suveere\" width=\"383\" height=\"264\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">However, India is a land of taboos and we are often prejudiced against freely talking about one’s feelings. Also, visiting a psychiatrist is made a huge issue in the society because the ignorant masses tend to believe that one visits a psychiatrist only when one goes ‘mad’. They are unaware of the fact that the word ‘mad’ doesn’t even exist in the lexicon of psychiatry and this ignorance has caused many young minds lose their lives.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A long path needs to be treaded before we can make the youth free from the burden of mental pressure and stress. We need to realize that there is no point in being a part of the rat race, graduating to being a no body and then ending up killing oneself. We need to realize and make the children realize that life is special and we should try to mould it the way we want to and then try to be happy in the work we do. Taking excess stress hasn’t helped anyone. Keeping a cool head and a determined goal on the other hand, can work miracles.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Today, the onus lies upon us. Our generation has been a part of the rat race and we are still running. We don’t want that for our next generation. For that, there is a need to be open- minded. We need to realize that unless and until we free ourselves from the shackles of mental stress and our race for money, we won’t be able to inculcate this thought in our progenies.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Attempts are on, many organizations are working relentlessly towards this mission and the results will start showing really soon. What we can do on our part is that we can start trying to be happy, freeing our minds from the narrow and negative thoughts, get a clear idea about our goals, be more determined mentally, remove all the taboos and start thanking life for the blessings it has bestowed upon us.</p>','How Easy is it to Kill Oneself ?','','publish','open','open','','easy-kill-oneself','','','2014-12-09 22:45:06','2014-12-09 17:15:06','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1900',0,'post','',1),(1902,2,'2014-12-09 22:36:49','2014-12-09 17:06:49','','helpiez','','inherit','open','open','','aaaaa','','','2014-12-09 22:36:49','2014-12-09 17:06:49','',1900,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/aaaaa.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1904,2,'2014-12-09 22:38:57','2014-12-09 17:08:57','','suveer','','inherit','open','open','','suveer','','','2014-12-09 22:38:57','2014-12-09 17:08:57','',1900,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/suveer.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1905,2,'2014-12-09 22:39:03','2014-12-09 17:09:03','','suveere','','inherit','open','open','','suveere','','','2014-12-09 22:39:03','2014-12-09 17:09:03','',1900,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/suveere.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1907,23,'2014-12-09 23:37:15','2014-12-09 18:07:15','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">There are some days, some moments that get engraved in your memory. No matter how hard you try, you can\'t convince your mind to get rid of them. And these memories stick around for much longer if they hurt you. Shatter you so completely, it starts feeling like the ruins of your old self prick you every now and then. As hard as you want to forget, you realize you remember the exact moment down to each detail.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">            Rodriguez went through a similar day, a similar moment when he was all of seven. It was a Sunday. It was church day.His mother wanted him to attend the mass. But he was just a child and it seemed like such a boring place. He could have done anything to stay at home. And when his uncle volunteered take care of him, he was more than happy to get out of his church situation. Though his uncle said, \'But you have to promise to be an obedient child.\' Rodriguez, happy to stay at home and watch television, agreed.  Without realizing what his uncle actually meant or what was about to happen to him. He didn\'t realise what had happened to him till years later when he decided to walk down the memory lane of a shattered childhood. After his mother left, Rodriguez and his uncle sat in front of the television to watch Batman. Rodriguez loved that show. He admired Batman for how he always helped people, delivered justice. And from that day onwards,  he wished for a real superhero. Somebody who\'d free him. Somebody who\'d deliver justice. After everything was done, Rodriguez realised that maybe the world wasn\'t painted in black and white. It was grey. And in this grey world, nobody could give him that white colored justice. For what his oppressor did was way too dark to be talked about. After some time, Rodriguez felt his uncle come close to him. A little too close. Close enough for Rodriguez to feel uncomfortable. He tried getting off the bed. But his uncle kept a hand on his mouth. Rodriguez was confused. His uncle took off his pants. And what followed was the rape of a seven year old child. He tried to scream but his uncle kept reminding him about his promise- he had to be an obedient child and eventually Rodriguez gave in. He went quiet.  He\'d stopped feeling anything. Everything around him went quiet. He could barely hear the television or his dog barking outside the closed bedroom door. Everything outside was as silent as he felt on the inside. He didn\'t start feeling anything again till his uncle was gone. And even after that, all he felt was his broken childhood ache. He was just seven. It\'s not how he wanted his first kiss to be. It\'s not how he wanted to lose his innocence. In the years to follow, he\'d be raped. Repeatedly. At times by four to five men. He\'d accepted his reality. He didn\'t have a single world to be in. In his head, he\'d compartmentalised. He started living in two worlds. One was that of an oppressed child, the other was that of a little boy trying to lead a normal life.He was accustomed to frequent visits by his uncle and his friends. The moment they were left alone, he\'d just take off his pants. Living through the horror, yet not feeling it till it was over. He could do nothing to stop it. The mother who traditionally is the fierce protector of her child, hushed him when he tried to tell her about it. She told him to never tell anybody about it. It\'s not what a family wants to hear about. It\'s too dark to be discussed.  Little kids don\'t talk about such dirty things. It\'s bad manners. Nothing made him cringe more. Even though he felt frustrated, he reminded himself the world was grey.It was only after some eleven years that he decided he\'d taken enough. He decided that he didn\'t want to be the victim anymore. That day, when his uncle entered the room, Rodriguez didn\'t take off his pants. His uncle tried to force himself upon Rodriguez. But Rodriguez pushed him. Screamed out. Said he\'d put up with it for too long and left. A kick that probably striked his uncle\'s conscience was all that he needed to stop it all. To take back control of his own life. And the day his uncle was on his deathbed, he went upto him. He wasn\'t looking at his uncle. He was looking at the man who\'d snatched away his childhood.He went upto him and said three words that he had to get off his chest. He couldn\'t carry these words with him all his life. He said, \' I forgive you.\'</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">And God knows, he hadn\'t felt this good all his life. He felt cleaner than ever. In that moment, he realized, he was his own hero and had gifted himself the white justice that nobody could give him. One of the two worlds he existed in, had ceased to exist. He wasn\'t the victim anymore. And the silence inside him, broke as he sat down and cried.</p>','Silence on the Inside','','publish','open','open','','silence-inside','','','2014-12-09 23:37:15','2014-12-09 18:07:15','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1907',0,'post','',1),(1908,2,'2014-12-09 23:35:30','2014-12-09 18:05:30','Honorable Mention Illustrative\n\nÒA ChildÕs Black CloudÓ by Staff Sgt. James D. Mossman, U.S. Air Force.\n\nThis photograph was done for a story on child abuse.  It is one of three photographs in a series and was taken with the intention off showing the fear and pain a child might experience at the hands of an abusive adult.','Child Abuse','','inherit','open','open','','child-abuse','','','2014-12-09 23:35:30','2014-12-09 18:05:30','',1907,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/child-abuse.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1914,23,'2014-12-11 16:33:16','2014-12-11 11:03:16','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It\'s raining and Seema sits inside the house. The house doesn\'t belong to her. It\'s the house she works in. As a maid. Seema isn\'t much older than ma\'amji\'s own daughter. She is thirteen and from Assam. Snatched away from her parents at age nine, she\'s been through a lot and carries much more experience than a thirteen year old. Being sexually assaulted by her kidnappers has left her with some marks both mental and physical. It isn\'t just that there are some memories that would remain engraved in her mind but also the ugly cigarette burns on her body that she earned by protesting against those who assaulted her.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Back home, she had a lot of dreams. She wanted to be a teacher. She didn\'t particularly like studying but she loved writing on the black board with a chalk. She wanted to fix the roof of her house which always leaked during rains. She had thought about helping her father in his farm work by buying him new implements. However,  she was forced to join the child labour community by those who kidnapped her. This child labour community isn\'t too small when talking in terms of India. It\'s that evil institution that forces young children to discard all their big and small dreams. Hence, Seema\'s eyes don\'t harbour any dreams now. She hasn\'t seen her family in years and misses them. Now, she only wishes that she can go back to home; that unlike her childhood, her home isn\'t forever lost.</p>','Childhood - Forever Lost','','publish','open','open','','childhood-forever-lost','','','2014-12-11 16:33:16','2014-12-11 11:03:16','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1914',0,'post','',0),(1915,19,'2014-12-11 15:55:30','2014-12-11 10:25:30','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Planning out a trip with friends? New year’s party passes? Want to buy a new dress or a latest gadget? Your wish-list bucket which goes on and on and if, the only problem which is stopping you from all this is MONEY??? Then, stop worrying!!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Be it teens to adults, college students to working people, every individual needs money to fulfil their wish-list, dreams and basic needs.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Money is a major factor in every person’s life. But this major factor should not interfere your quality of life. Yes, there are no shortcuts to earn money. If there are, they only corresponds to risk and nothing else. But there are few sure shot tricks you need to tag on that can save up a lot of money without any risk. All you have to do is follow few smart steps that can leave your pocket filled with notes to spend, save and invest on your wish-list and on your needs. And, what can be better for all time-strapped people if you have to spare just 5 minutes for that?  Great, isn’t it?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images1.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1925\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images1.png\" alt=\"images\" width=\"284\" height=\"177\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">So, here are 10 simple and not-so time consuming tips to save money—</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>1) Say no to unwanted things: </strong>Stop buying random things which you really don’t want and don’t like. Grab your favourite and useful things rather than some superfluous things.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>2) Home is the best place : </strong>Want to give a treat? Then why to go out when you can organise a 5-star like party at your place without investing much of money. Invite your friends instead of going out to some expensive club.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>3) Avoid late payments : </strong>Whether you have to pay the phone bill, electricity bill or the institution bill in which you are studying, pay on time. Avoiding  bill payments on time will lead to extra payment. So avoid it.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>4) Sign up rewards programme : </strong>Be it a bank or any shopping and grocery store, don’t miss out any reward programmes which can fetch you discounts and redeem your earned points.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>5) Re-pair &amp; Re-use</strong> : Use some creativity to use the used, old and damaged things. It will not only bring your hidden talent out but will save a lot of money. Try it, it works.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>6) Sell out unnecessary things : </strong>Don’t need an item anymore? Then why to keep it unnecessary, SELL OUT! Go to a site where you can give ads and look for buyers who wants to buy it.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>7) Give up expensive bad habits- </strong>Quit the bad habits like smoking and drinking. These habits will make your money to flow away from you with nothing in return. So put a full stop to these habits. It will not only increase your life span and make you healthy but will also put a stop to your burning and floating pocket.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>8) Use Public transports or Carpool : </strong>If public transportation facility is available near you, then use it. Or anyone who stays near by and travels on the same route, share rides by alternatively driving each day. This saves money as the public transportation is far cheap and carpooling will save a lot of fuel and hence, your wallet.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>9) Open an account in a good interest-giving bank : </strong>Don’t open an account in a bank which doesn’t provide  good interest rate to you. Invest and save money in such a bank which has good interest rate programme.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>10) Drink lot of  water</strong>: Yes, funny but it is one of the simplest tips. Drinking plenty of water not only keeps your health in a good state but will also help in filling your stomach. Hence, it will reduce the food bill.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Whenever the struggle against money feels like a burden, browse a personal finance site or a blog and read it. Don’t forget there are many people who are going through the same. Go through the archives of views and learn something different and new.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Make smart choices!  Take smart chances!  Welcome better changes!</p>','10 Small steps to save money','','publish','open','open','','10-small-steps-save-money','','','2014-12-11 15:55:30','2014-12-11 10:25:30','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1915',0,'post','',2),(1917,2,'2014-12-11 15:35:24','2014-12-11 10:05:24','','Indian_FlagELIV','','inherit','open','open','','indian_flageliv','','','2014-12-11 15:35:24','2014-12-11 10:05:24','',1837,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/indian_flageliv.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1919,2,'2014-12-11 15:46:32','2014-12-11 10:16:32','','images','','inherit','open','open','','images-17','','','2014-12-11 15:46:32','2014-12-11 10:16:32','',1915,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images4.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1920,2,'2014-12-11 15:46:43','2014-12-11 10:16:43','','images (1)','','inherit','open','open','','images-1-5','','','2014-12-11 15:46:43','2014-12-11 10:16:43','',1915,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-15.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1921,2,'2014-12-11 15:46:54','2014-12-11 10:16:54','','images (2)','','inherit','open','open','','images-2-4','','','2014-12-11 15:46:54','2014-12-11 10:16:54','',1915,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-22.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1922,2,'2014-12-11 15:48:03','2014-12-11 10:18:03','','download','','inherit','open','open','','download-5','','','2014-12-11 15:48:03','2014-12-11 10:18:03','',1915,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/download2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1924,2,'2014-12-11 15:49:36','2014-12-11 10:19:36','','images (3)','','inherit','open','open','','images-3-4','','','2014-12-11 15:49:36','2014-12-11 10:19:36','',1915,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-32.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1925,2,'2014-12-11 15:50:44','2014-12-11 10:20:44','','images','','inherit','open','open','','images-18','','','2014-12-11 15:50:44','2014-12-11 10:20:44','',1915,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1926,2,'2014-12-11 15:50:59','2014-12-11 10:20:59','','???????????????????????????????????????????????????','','inherit','open','open','','1926','','','2014-12-11 15:50:59','2014-12-11 10:20:59','',1915,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/businessman-save-money-putting-coin-piggy-bank-33131491.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1928,12,'2014-12-11 16:24:27','2014-12-11 10:54:27','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Should we actually be proud to call ourselves technologically advanced? This is a question to be given serious thought about. The first answer that comes to our mind is that yes, definitely technology has made us think beyond whatever we are capable of thinking, and do beyond whatever we are capable of doing. But technology has nevertheless pushed us far aside from being emotionally cooperative and responsible citizens.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/lkj.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1929\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/lkj.jpg\" alt=\"lkj\" width=\"480\" height=\"350\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We have forgotten how it’s like to be in a park, talking to or making new friends. We often become so obsessed with our cell phones and other gadgets that we don’t even notice the person sitting next to you while travelling to some place. We have forgotten how to use libraries and refer from books. Books have become long gone friends who occasionally visit during exams. Google and Wikipedia do give us information at a much faster pace. But while browsing we don’t just look through the information but also at other social networking and other sites. Such multitasking is often not desired, especially in the case of academics. Technology, although it has made life easier, has brought along with it certain distractions which are often disregarded.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Another important aspect which comes into picture is that technology hinders the imaginative power of people. Parents don’t find time to read out stories to their children. They are put to sleep by giving them mobile phones to play with or even other video games. Even in cartoons, the characters are projected to be technologically much more advanced that while growing up itself children are made to believe that life is a lot easier with technology around. Gone are the days where children used to read books and play with each other imagining themselves to be characters in it. Technology can also lead to ill effects in health as long hours in front of the computer or TV could lead to eating disorders or obesity. Technology comes at the cost of exercises. Hence if we don’t take a conscious effort to exercise and keep ourselves healthy, technology will take over and destroy it.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1930\" src=\"http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/cvb.jpg\" alt=\"cvb\" width=\"600\" height=\"350\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is true that through social networking sites, we get to be in touch with far away friends and family. But it has, at the same time pushed us away from having actual quality time spent with them.Technology is a boon as it has made human kind advance in life like none other. It has made life easier and faster. But it should not occupy such an important role in our life that we forget our roots and leap towards modernity.</p>','Technology: A boon or a bane?','','publish','open','open','','technology-boon-bane','','','2014-12-11 16:24:27','2014-12-11 10:54:27','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1928',0,'post','',1),(1929,2,'2014-12-11 16:02:29','2014-12-11 10:32:29','','lkj','','inherit','open','open','','lkj','','','2014-12-11 16:02:29','2014-12-11 10:32:29','',1928,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/lkj.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1930,2,'2014-12-11 16:03:39','2014-12-11 10:33:39','','cvb','','inherit','open','open','','cvb','','','2014-12-11 16:03:39','2014-12-11 10:33:39','',1928,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/cvb.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1932,2,'2014-12-11 16:13:04','2014-12-11 10:43:04','','download (1)','','inherit','open','open','','download-1-4','','','2014-12-11 16:13:04','2014-12-11 10:43:04','',1928,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/download-14.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1933,2,'2014-12-11 16:14:22','2014-12-11 10:44:22','','images (4)','','inherit','open','open','','images-4-4','','','2014-12-11 16:14:22','2014-12-11 10:44:22','',1928,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-42.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1934,2,'2014-12-11 16:15:26','2014-12-11 10:45:26','','images (5)','','inherit','open','open','','images-5-3','','','2014-12-11 16:15:26','2014-12-11 10:45:26','',1928,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/images-52.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1936,2,'2014-12-11 16:20:57','2014-12-11 10:50:57','','5new-prometheus_050312','','inherit','open','open','','5new-prometheus_050312','','','2014-12-11 16:20:57','2014-12-11 10:50:57','',1928,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/5new-prometheus_050312.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1940,2,'2014-12-11 16:53:28','2014-12-11 11:23:28','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Poverty is a widespread problem of India with nearly one fourth of its population (nearly equal to US population) living below poverty line. India is home to one third of poor in world. It is one of the three countries among 81 developing nations where Global Hunger Index has increased. It is often commented that the growth of India is dichotomous, it is both an emerging economic giant as well as a land of impoverished. Wealth distribution is so uneven that top 10% of income group earns 32% of income. So the burning problem we face is not just to grow economically but also socially otherwise it can lead to social unrest. Schemes like MNREGA, Swarna Jayanti Gram Swarojgar Yojna have been beset by scandals and are slow in outreach, owing to mismanagement and rampant corruption.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Whenever the traditional model does not satisfies the needs of society, innovation is demanded. Hence Social Entrepreneurship (SE) is the need of hour. It contributes tremendously in creating a culture of social innovation among communities. In fact SE accounts for 1% of GDP in UK. There can be various faces of it. I would like to illustrate one example in this context.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The pressure to migrate to urban areas for earning livelihood is one of the biggest problems of poor across India. It leaves their family back in village redundant of any economic activity and dependent on wages earned by them. Single breadwinner, who most probably will be living in  fragile condition in some  slum , succumb to the pressure of managing such large family with meager means, and end up either in vicious circle of debt or get involved in illegal activities.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If the employment opportunity can be provided at the native place only, which suits their skills and ability, it would be a better economical as well as social solution. For instance, we can promote rural tourism to empower the rural economy creating a sustainable indigenous method for reducing migration. All this while preserving and promoting national heritage of country and sharing it with next generation.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Investment can be encouraged to generate measurable social and environmental impact alongside a financial return. Also by encouraging Small Scale Industries, strict government laws on import of products which can be produced at local scale industry can boost rural employment.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I think that the time is ripe for India to focus on its development issues-It stands at a cross road in its fight against poverty, systematic corruption, lack of strong leadership. But the unbridled energy and infinite potential of Indian youth gives ray of hope. With researches expounding the benefit of India’s JUGAAD innovation culture, there is no shortage of innovative ideas to fund. I would like to end on a key note by Pro Bono Economics that we can eliminate poverty completely by 2030 by Social Entrepreneurship and Small Scale Industries.</p>','Poverty Elimination using Social Entrepreneurship','','publish','open','open','','poverty-elimination-using-social-entrepreneurship','','','2014-12-11 16:53:28','2014-12-11 11:23:28','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1940',0,'post','',0),(1941,2,'2014-12-11 16:30:23','2014-12-11 11:00:23','','childhood-wallpaper-1280x800','','inherit','open','open','','childhood-wallpaper-1280x800','','','2014-12-11 16:30:23','2014-12-11 11:00:23','',1914,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/childhood-wallpaper-1280x800.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1944,2,'2014-12-11 16:50:19','2014-12-11 11:20:19','','1477034_orig','','inherit','open','open','','1477034_orig','','','2014-12-11 16:50:19','2014-12-11 11:20:19','',1940,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/1477034_orig.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1947,23,'2014-12-11 18:26:39','2014-12-11 12:56:39','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I am a woman. I have to walk on the roads very carefully. Well, the traffic in this country is a little rebellious and quick to break rules but I have different reasons for being so paranoid while walking on the roads. I am always looking over my shoulder to make sure nobody is following me. I keep looking ahead to make sure nobody is waiting for me in the next alley. I have mastered the art of being perfectly aware about my surroundings. However, the news is often a rude reminder- it often reminds me that I can be attacked from anywhere. Not just the roads but sitting at my home or at work or while travelling. Basically, it\'s just not a safe place for me because I happen to be a girl. I hear about a girl being brutally raped by 5 men and left to die or about a girl who was shot because she chose to adhere to the rules and did not serve a drink to the son of a powerful politician. On a lesser charge, a brave girl dragged a man who was trying to sexually assault her in a metro. A metro that was full of people. How long do we put up with this mentality? How long do we live in fear? How long till one of us is attacked and made the next headline for about a month?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This Indian mentality that which allows for men to do whatever they want with women walking down the road needs to change. They don\'t care about our clothes or about how much chowmein we had, they just look at us as creatures of prey. A famous politician said boy will be boys and they make mistakes. This comment reflects the attitude of the entire country towards how women ought to be treated. If boys will be boys, what are girls supposed to be? If raped, we become dented and painted.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I would love to end on an optimistic note about how things are slowly changing and we\'re becoming more \'modern\' but as a girl living in India, I know that\'s far from the reality. It\'ll take a lot more sacrifices for the mentality of people to actually change. As a frustrated young Indian,  I can tell you it\'s not fun to live in fear about being the next girl shot at work or about becoming a victim to 5 drunk men or being sexually assaulted while travelling. I hope for change and I pray, each day, that I don\'t become a prey to the creatures or that I don\'t become the next sacrifice.</p>','Need for Change','','publish','open','open','','need-change','','','2014-12-11 18:26:39','2014-12-11 12:56:39','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1947',0,'post','',0),(1953,25,'2014-12-12 08:10:08','2014-12-12 02:40:08','It is during this period that you come to know more about yourself. What is that period? Are there multiple answers or just one? If you ask any graduating student the answer is just one.It is that time when you are looking for someone to hire you. It is this time when you start analising your strengths, weaknesses, long term goals and you also look back to see what all you have done till now. Classes, labs, assignments, exams, vivas - none of these can assess your actual IQ and EQ than this process.\n\nYou may not realize how the extra academic activities, the late night studies, games and the things you did just for fun turn the other way round to help you more than your CGPA during an interview. The only thing that needs to be done by you is the preparation to present you at that very moment. During the college life you might have bothered only about how many marks you get on a scale of 100. This is the phase you should get ready to face either a ‘0’ or a ‘100’.\n\nDo not get depressed if you are rejected. Perceive that to be a loss of that company because you know that you won’t stop trying till you get in to one and this will be surely an extra opportunity for you to learn more and come up stronger the next time. The days may seem longer and you may be filled with anxiety about life more than ever. Do not panic and try to enjoy these days as every other day. And once this storm is over, you won’t remember how you made through it, you won’t be the same person who walked in. Later you may find yourself giving incentives to others. That’s what this storm is all about.\n\nOne of the things that adds to this storm is the pressure from your Family or Relatives and their expectations on the package. As a son/daughter it is your responsibility to satisfy your parents’ wish and as a parent it is their responsibility to honour your struggle for it. Just leave the rest of them and go for a job which you will never find disinteresting. Welcome, the future of India to the real world!','Are you in search of finding who you are?','','publish','open','open','','search-finding','','','2014-12-12 08:10:08','2014-12-12 02:40:08','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1953',0,'post','',0),(1954,2,'2014-12-12 00:49:41','2014-12-11 19:19:41','','download (2)','','inherit','open','open','','download-2-3','','','2014-12-12 00:49:41','2014-12-11 19:19:41','',1953,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/download-22.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1957,2,'2014-12-12 08:05:24','2014-12-12 02:35:24','','jobs','','inherit','open','open','','jobs-2','','','2014-12-12 08:05:24','2014-12-12 02:35:24','',1953,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/jobs.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1959,26,'2014-12-12 08:31:05','2014-12-12 03:01:05','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When the ‘Kiss of Love’ protest started, the opposition started spreading that kissing, public display of affection, etc. are against Indian culture and several similar things and how the idea of the protest is preposterous. Several articles in newspapers and posts in social media mentioned how the Indian youth was trying to copy western culture under the pretence of modernity. The opposition said today the protesters are protesting for kissing in public and tomorrow they would protest for having sex in public. Several religious and political groups like the Shiv Sena, RSS, Bajrang Dal, Hanuman Sena, and all kinds of dals and senas resorted to violence to save their very pious and clean Indian culture from the clutches of the immoral and dirty so-called Western culture. This protest and anti-protest spread to several parts of India and the Indian media made the Indian public see how the protest was being organised by the supporters and how it was being disorganised by the opposition.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">And in between all this madness, it was blissfully forgotten the main aim of the protests, i.e., moral policing and mostly everybody condemned the mere act of kissing. I do not remember reading a single newspaper article or a single post in social media that said anything about moral policing, forget about supporting or opposing. Everybody pointed fingers that a protest was being held and so many people were kissing each other in public and destroying the sanctity of Indian culture. It was forgotten that the protest was against moral policing, and that too a peaceful one and so many people kissing each other was just a way of protesting. Nobody mentioned that the acts of moral policing were not only absurd, but outright disgusting and against the freedom of humanity. The idea that someone protesting for simple public displays of affection like hugging or kissing in public would, in future, protest for having sex in public is preposterous.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The thing is India is a great land of hypocrites. Those bellowing the most that the western culture is destroying Indian culture have in fact the least knowledge about Indian culture. A facebook post showing pictures of white people doing yoga and Indians participating in the Kiss of Love protest said how the west was trying to copy what made India great and how Indians were trying to copy the thing what degraded the west. I am 100% sure the people who shared the post would themselves not be having a grain of knowledge about yoga, forget about practicing it. And the idea that kissing or public display of affection has degraded or would degrade a culture is simply crazy. Again, I am equally sure the people belonging to the religious groups protesting that their religion is being harmed by western culture would not have read a single page of the Quran or the Gita or the Bible or any of their religious text.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Indians need to clearly understand that the only thing degrading their great pure Indian culture is their habit of uselessly interfering into others’ matters and not minding their own business.</p>','A “KISS OF LOVE” OR “SLAP OF HYPOCRISY”','','publish','open','open','','kiss-love-slap-hypocrisy','','','2014-12-12 08:31:05','2014-12-12 03:01:05','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1959',0,'post','',1),(1960,2,'2014-12-12 08:28:43','2014-12-12 02:58:43','','kj','','inherit','open','open','','kj','','','2014-12-12 08:28:43','2014-12-12 02:58:43','',1959,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/kj.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1964,13,'2014-12-12 08:46:35','2014-12-12 03:16:35','                      \n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Many a times we are told that we should exercise daily, but every time we try we end up just doing it for not more than 2 weeks. Exercise is something in which regularity pays off. Doing more exercise is snot important but doing exercise daily is what matters the most which most of the people just loose at some point of time. We already know various benefits of exercise and we exercise for ourselves only. It’s not like that we can transfer the hard effort of one’s exercise on someone else like money. If one want’s to get fit then it is his/her duty to exercise daily otherwise, he wouldn’t be able to get various benefits of exercise:-</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Exercise controls weight</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The first and the foremost benefit of exercise is that it controls weight. People are in a dilemma that exercise only helps to lose weight but rather it also helps in increasing one’s weight or body mass. By weight we are referring to the body mass not the fats and carbohydrates exactly. Exercise helps in increasing the strength in body and increase its mass. It also help the fat people to lose their fat from various parts of the body which will definitely help them in one or the other way at some point of time.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Exercise combats health conditions and diseases</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> At the age of 40 people normally suffers from various diseases like diabetes, blood pressure etc. You will be amazed by knowing that these diseases can easily be cured or combated through the help of daily exercise. Daily exercise increase the circulation of blood and oxygen in body which keeps every muscle in the body at work. It utilizes the excess fat or any other resource that can cause harm to the body in one or the other way because “Excess of everything is bad”.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> <strong>Exercise improves mood</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> People do pub, watch movie or go to the concert in order to get a break from the daily routine of the life. I say that daily exercise will help us on utilizing our time more efficiently and smartly. Exercise just have a magical effect on our body that we tends to forget the problems in our lives. When we take some time out from our routine for ourselves it feels great and when we do it daily it just improves our mood and let us deal with our daily problem. Our mind will be cool and calm at one time.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> <strong>Exercise boosts energy</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> If we put our muscles to daily use then it not only gives us strength but also boosts our power by a notifiable scale. Exercise improves our muscles strength and size.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> <strong>Exercise promotes better sleep</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> Being insomniac is not one wants but it is so hard to get a good sleep in this hectic life. Sleep is nothing but is a natural phenomenon when our body rests and regains the energy. Being surrounded by the latest technologies and tech that helps us to reduce our efforts doesn’t make the full utilize the body and hence our body doesn’t get tired at all, as a result body doesn’t feel to rest I.e. have a sleep. Exercise will make use of the unused muscles in the body and finally when the body gets tired we can get a good tight sleep.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> <strong>The bottom line on exercise</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> Exercise and physical activity are a great way to feel better, gain health benefits and have fun. As a general goal, aim for at least 30 minutes of physical activity every day. If you want to lose weight or meet specific fitness goals, you may need to exercise more. Remember to check with your doctor before starting a new exercise program, especially if you haven\'t exercised for a long time, have chronic health problems, such as heart disease, diabetes or arthritis, or you have any concerns.</p>','Why we should Exercise?','','publish','open','open','','exercise','','','2014-12-12 08:46:35','2014-12-12 03:16:35','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1964',0,'post','',0),(1965,2,'2014-12-12 08:46:01','2014-12-12 03:16:01','','the-body-achieves-what-the-mind-believes','','inherit','open','open','','the-body-achieves-what-the-mind-believes','','','2014-12-12 08:46:01','2014-12-12 03:16:01','',1964,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/the-body-achieves-what-the-mind-believes.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1969,18,'2014-12-12 14:18:31','2014-12-12 08:48:31','','loud','','inherit','open','open','','loud','','','2014-12-12 14:18:31','2014-12-12 08:48:31','',1837,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/loud.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1979,27,'2014-12-13 08:45:03','2014-12-13 03:15:03','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">So, it happened again. God knows how many unfortunate crimes will take place before the slumbering authorities awaken. I don’t understand what are they waiting for? With so many cases coming up, women safety should be of utmost importance at this point in time. But our government is busy looking for ways to cast away their responsibility and put the blame on someone else’s shoulders.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If we look at the Delhi’s Uber cab case, same happened there as well. Instead of accepting full responsibility for the loop holes in the system, government thought their work is done by blaming Uber and posing a ban against them. Undoubtedly, the Uber Company is at fault. There is a serious concern regarding their background check process. But, banning Uber Company is not the only thing that needs to be done in the case. Proper investigation is called for to look into the fact that how come a two time rape convict was out on bail, driving a reputed company’s cab, which is thought to be a safe way to commute. Not only was he a serious threat to our society but his freedom was a mockery to all those victims who knock at our legal system’s door in search of justice.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A lot has to be done in order to make our country safe for the fairer sex. People with criminal intentions are not afraid of committing a crime as they are sure of getting away with it. There have been past incidents in which criminals were subjected to imprisonment of few years. Their identity was not even revealed, they did not lose much from a social perspective. Served few years in prison and then came back to lead a normal life. If we look at stats, we will find that in most of the cases, convicts are repeat offenders and they are used to it.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The convict in Uber Cab’s case has accepted that he had targeted several women who hired his cab, all those cases remained unreported. This clearly shows the victim’s distrust in our legal system. If we go by current trend, nothing much would have happened even if all those cases were reported. As the accused was already acquitted of one of the cases reported in 2011. Now, the Delhi police is describing him as a <em>“Psychotic Criminal”.</em> Even if he is psychotic then why was he out on bail? Why his mental illness was not captured in the last investigation? Why did police grant him freedom to commit more crimes? All these facts clearly points in the same direction that our legal system is in need of amendment, as current laws are obviously not serving their purpose. Stern action should be taken against such heinous crimes, which would set an example for all the criminal minded people.  Imposing strict laws to invoke fear in the minds of wrongdoers can be a good start.</p>','An Awakening Call - High time to initiate the change','','publish','open','open','','awakening-call-high-time-initiate-change','','','2014-12-13 08:45:03','2014-12-13 03:15:03','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1979',0,'post','',2),(1980,2,'2014-12-13 08:41:20','2014-12-13 03:11:20','','hg','','inherit','open','open','','hg','','','2014-12-13 08:41:20','2014-12-13 03:11:20','',1979,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/hg.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1983,2,'2014-12-13 09:20:52','2014-12-13 09:20:52','&nbsp;\n\n“All men are the same. Cheaters!”  Shalini said while she was crying.\n\n“Not all are the same Shalu, Stop crying!” I consoled.\n\nIn this time, where feminists are fighting for their rights, I’ve always fought for men being generalized as rapists, perverts, cheaters, liars etc. Yes, there should be no discrimination based on gender and yes, a girl’s clothes can never be the reason of rape, but what is done by a few men, cannot be the basis to judge all of them.\n\nWomen have become so unsafe in this country that they have stopped trusting men. That is acceptable. But generalizing the fact that all men are untrustworthy, all are rapists and all are disrespectful towards women, that is unacceptable. There is a proverb in Hindi “<em>Ek gandi macchli saare talaab ko ganda kar deti hai” </em>(One rotten fish contaminates the whole pond), this is what is happening with men too. Done by a few men, but all are accused of those crimes. Is it fair? We talk about feminism, but isn’t this totally unfair? What about those innocent men who had fought to save the girls? Does labeling men solve all the problems?\n\nI read a post where a guy was beaten up by women because they thought that he is trying to eve-tease a girl. But later they got to know that he was just trying to offer a girl his seat because she was standing. Now this is the scene I am talking about. Why should innocent men suffer? The bad ones roaming free and the innocent ones are beaten up for doing well.\n\nThis has to change, SOON. This attitude of the “FEMINISTS” has to change, because this won’t make things better in this country, ita would simply make it worse.','All Men Are Not The Same','','publish','open','open','','men-not','','','2014-12-13 09:20:52','2014-12-13 09:20:52','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?p=1983',0,'post','',2),(1984,2,'2014-12-13 09:07:23','2014-12-13 03:37:23','','GoodWife','','inherit','open','open','','goodwife','','','2014-12-13 09:07:23','2014-12-13 03:37:23','',1983,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/goodwife.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1985,2,'2014-12-13 09:19:17','2014-12-13 03:49:17','','GoodWife','','inherit','open','open','','goodwife-2','','','2014-12-13 09:19:17','2014-12-13 03:49:17','',1983,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/goodwife1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2025,2,'2014-06-05 16:53:11','2014-06-05 16:53:11','With 3.3 million NGO\'s present in India, we still have a dearth of volunteers who volunteer for change, for turning the society a better place to live in. In this modern age of technology, people seldom have information that would, on one hand, make them approach the concerned NGO themselves and on the other hand, make them motivated enough to try and make our society a better place.\n\nThus, Helpiez, was created to revolutionize the outreach of social service in India by creating a web portal for those who are dedicated to people and are interested in working for benefit of the society.\n\nWe are designing a user-friendly, interactive website through which the users, especially the youth with their extensive social circles and network can connect to welfare organizations and the society.The web portal will feature customizable search options for all the projects, programs, volunteering events, internships or jobs related to NGOs etc. It will also have a separate profile for each organization which they get to manage according to their needs.\n\nHelpiez,sincerely believes in the cause of bridging the wide gap between the motivated volunteers and the different NGO\'s supporting different causes. This portal will directly help welfare organizations in increasing their online presence which will enable people to look through their agenda and contribute correspondingly. Hence, it will increase awareness in the society for both the Cause and about the NGO which works for the Cause.\n\nThrough Helpiez, the social developers of the present will find a new platform to raise their concerns from and on the other hand it will also make the volunteering more efficient and easily available to the people. This social venture in the long run and in many ways will take community service in India to a whole new level and giving it the required push. We, at Helpiez shall bring together those people who demand a social change and make world a better place for future generations.','Our Vision','','publish','open','open','','vision','','','2014-06-05 16:53:11','2014-06-05 16:53:11','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/?page_id=46',0,'page','',0),(2035,2,'2014-12-20 11:16:36','2014-12-20 11:16:36','','Home','','publish','open','open','','home','','','2014-12-20 11:16:36','2014-12-20 11:16:36','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/blog/?page_id=2035',0,'page','',0),(2050,2,'2014-12-20 11:45:48','2014-12-20 11:45:48','','white computer keyboard with the red button help','','inherit','open','open','','white-computer-keyboard-with-the-red-button-help','','','2014-12-20 11:45:48','2014-12-20 11:45:48','',1575,'http://ec2-52-6-199-128.compute-1.amazonaws.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/help.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2106,2,'2014-12-20 17:31:29','2014-12-20 17:31:29','[wppb-edit-profile]','Edit Profile','','publish','open','open','','edit-profile','','','2014-12-20 17:31:29','2014-12-20 17:31:29','',0,'http://www.helpiez.org/blog/?page_id=2106',0,'page','',0),(2108,2,'2014-12-20 17:33:53','2014-12-20 17:33:53','[wordpress_social_login] [su_lightbox type=\"inline\" src=\"#edit\"][button size=\"small\" text_size=\"gamma\"]Edit Profile[/button][/su_lightbox] [su_lightbox type=\"inline\" src=\"#article\"][button size=\"small\" text_size=\"gamma\"]Submit Your Article[/button][/su_lightbox] [su_lightbox_content id=\"edit\"][wppb-edit-profile][/su_lightbox_content] [su_lightbox_content id=\"article\"][contact-form-7 id=\"2210\" title=\"Untitled\"][/su_lightbox_content]\n<div style=\"width:298px; margin-top:30px;\">[wppb-login]</div>','Dashboard','','publish','open','open','','login','','','2014-12-20 17:33:53','2014-12-20 17:33:53',